WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:42.609 --> 00:00:44.839
The future...

3
00:00:44.921 --> 00:00:47.520
The polar ice caps
have melted.

4
00:00:47.595 --> 00:00:49.862
covering the earth with water.

5
00:00:50.631 --> 00:00:55.400
Those who survived
have adapted

6
00:00:55.474 --> 00:00:57.457
to a new world.

7
00:05:39.000 --> 00:05:40.961
Bad luck. English.

8
00:05:42.282 --> 00:05:46.332
But the Slavers are producing
a good grade of poxy these days.

9
00:05:47.055 --> 00:05:50.562
Cost you a handful of dirt
or maybe that wind chime.

10
00:05:50.642 --> 00:05:52.061
What are you doing here?

11
00:05:52.132 --> 00:05:53.989
Just waiting.

12
00:05:54.061 --> 00:05:56.184
Take your hand off the sail.

13
00:05:57.209 --> 00:05:58.823
Take it off!

14
00:05:59.781 --> 00:06:03.796
I've seen your boat before.
Haven't seen you.

15
00:06:04.384 --> 00:06:05.872
Took it legal.

16
00:06:07.227 --> 00:06:10.573
Previous owner was dead
on the tiller when I found it.

17
00:06:10.646 --> 00:06:13.623
You had another hour
before I traded up again.

18
00:06:14.538 --> 00:06:16.188
Just improving my means.

19
00:06:17.448 --> 00:06:18.867
Well. I owe you then.

20
00:06:18.937 --> 00:06:20.148
No. thanks.

21
00:06:20.224 --> 00:06:24.817
I got all the supplies I need.
Just came from an atoll.

22
00:06:25.775 --> 00:06:28.475
Eight days east.
if you're interested.

23
00:06:30.479 --> 00:06:33.005
Two Drifters meet. something
needs to be exchanged.

24
00:06:33.086 --> 00:06:36.698
I know the code. But I'll
give you this one for free.

25
00:06:38.636 --> 00:06:40.563
Nothing's free in Waterworld.

26
00:06:41.242 --> 00:06:42.626
Yeah.

27
00:06:53.427 --> 00:06:54.846
Smokers.

28
00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:58.316
Just enough wind
to get away clean.

29
00:07:02.230 --> 00:07:04.150
Forget the bag.

30
00:07:08.062 --> 00:07:11.994
It's not worth it. You'll never
make it with your sails down.

31
00:07:12.072 --> 00:07:13.257
Hey!

32
00:07:26.388 --> 00:07:27.935
What can I say?

33
00:07:48.160 --> 00:07:49.910
Joe. he's going for it.

34
00:07:49.983 --> 00:07:51.304
What the hell?

35
00:07:56.677 --> 00:07:58.721
Never seen that before.

36
00:08:02.642 --> 00:08:04.822
Here we go! Go!
Drive! Drive!

37
00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:11.581
Faster! Faster!

38
00:08:33.362 --> 00:08:35.972
Come on! He's gonna get
it! He's gonna get it!

39
00:08:55.864 --> 00:08:58.044
Go!
Get him! Get him!

40
00:09:26.087 --> 00:09:27.306
No! No!

41
00:09:40.635 --> 00:09:42.373
No!

42
00:10:30.000 --> 00:10:33.158
How many ways can I say it?
Go on. hit the swells.

43
00:10:38.480 --> 00:10:41.113
What do you think? He
does have a bush on him.

44
00:10:41.210 --> 00:10:44.309
Cut a side barter if you
want. but don't open the gates.

45
00:10:48.007 --> 00:10:51.266
Inbound!
Straight out.

46
00:11:15.000 --> 00:11:16.380
English.

47
00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:23.437
Flag's down. Drifter.
We got enough traders.

48
00:11:31.335 --> 00:11:32.898
What does he have?

49
00:11:36.300 --> 00:11:38.656
Open the gates!

50
00:11:38.500 --> 00:11:39.050
Dirt.

51
00:12:41.000 --> 00:12:45.678
Bones to berries.
Veins to vine.

52
00:12:45.752 --> 00:12:49.569
These tendons to trees.
This blood to brine.

53
00:12:49.641 --> 00:12:51.690
Too old she was.

54
00:12:51.767 --> 00:12:56.242
This woman does leave us.
recycled and enshrined

55
00:12:56.321 --> 00:12:58.971
in the presence of him
who leads us.

56
00:13:18.820 --> 00:13:20.075
What is that?

57
00:13:26.000 --> 00:13:27.326
You know me?

58
00:13:28.662 --> 00:13:30.521
I know what you are.

59
00:13:30.593 --> 00:13:31.681
Good.

60
00:13:32.222 --> 00:13:34.683
Then you know if you look
for trouble while you're here.

61
00:13:34.752 --> 00:13:37.009
you'll find more
than you can handle.

62
00:13:38.015 --> 00:13:39.670
You got two hours.

63
00:13:42.974 --> 00:13:44.527
I'll only need one.

64
00:13:56.288 --> 00:13:58.307
He's coming over here.

65
00:14:03.212 --> 00:14:04.936
Me.
You each get one

66
00:14:05.007 --> 00:14:07.399
if everything's here
when I get back.

67
00:14:16.192 --> 00:14:17.381
Pure dirt.

68
00:14:18.621 --> 00:14:20.515
3.2 kilos.

69
00:14:22.848 --> 00:14:24.934
How'd you come by
so much of it?

70
00:14:26.277 --> 00:14:28.794
Another atoll 30 horizons
west of here.

71
00:14:28.872 --> 00:14:30.357
Where'd they get it?

72
00:14:31.402 --> 00:14:32.796
They didn't say.

73
00:14:32.867 --> 00:14:36.656
We heard about that
place. that they was all killed.

74
00:14:38.525 --> 00:14:40.917
That's why they didn't say.
Smokers?

75
00:14:40.988 --> 00:14:43.472
Maybe Smokers.
maybe Slavers.

76
00:14:45.448 --> 00:14:48.737
So what's the word?
We trading or not?

77
00:14:48.810 --> 00:14:53.132
We'll tally it
like pure hydro.

78
00:14:56.899 --> 00:14:59.859
Works out to 62 chits.

79
00:15:02.822 --> 00:15:04.511
I want twice that.

80
00:15:11.111 --> 00:15:13.130
You drive
a hard bargain.

81
00:15:32.878 --> 00:15:34.000
Dirt?

82
00:15:35.542 --> 00:15:37.527
I have never seen purer.

83
00:15:38.869 --> 00:15:41.058
I just want
one sip of hydro!

84
00:15:41.132 --> 00:15:43.117
No.
not till you tell me.

85
00:15:43.195 --> 00:15:46.621
She got inkings on her back.
I seen her.

86
00:15:46.691 --> 00:15:50.082
They say if you read
the marks on the child.

87
00:15:50.153 --> 00:15:53.046
they'll lead you
all the way to Dryland.

88
00:15:53.114 --> 00:15:54.803
Dryland's a myth.

89
00:15:54.878 --> 00:15:56.339
Some still believe.

90
00:15:56.410 --> 00:15:59.665
They say the Smokers even
got an eye out for her.

91
00:16:01.202 --> 00:16:04.457
Well. then. we'd better
keep it to ourselves.

92
00:16:38.980 --> 00:16:40.704
Help you?
Yeah.

93
00:16:41.743 --> 00:16:43.704
Where's the store?
You found it.

94
00:16:49.998 --> 00:16:51.483
You don't have much.

95
00:16:52.992 --> 00:16:54.716
You the man with the dirt?

96
00:16:57.752 --> 00:17:00.077
I'll take a hydro.
All six G's.

97
00:17:05.807 --> 00:17:08.199
Got any canvas? Line?

98
00:17:09.569 --> 00:17:12.688
Well. we've got line.
It's hair. No canvas.

99
00:17:13.096 --> 00:17:14.853
I'll take the line.

100
00:17:15.825 --> 00:17:17.480
Any seeds?
Nope.

101
00:17:19.319 --> 00:17:20.747
Wood?
Nope.

102
00:17:24.578 --> 00:17:25.563
Magazines?

103
00:17:25.645 --> 00:17:29.730
If I had a magazine.
I'd retire.

104
00:17:41.120 --> 00:17:42.877
Something to drink?

105
00:17:44.050 --> 00:17:45.535
Cup of hydro.

106
00:17:58.095 --> 00:17:59.217
Pure.

107
00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:19.230
Skoal.

108
00:18:23.155 --> 00:18:24.820
One more.
Make it two.

109
00:18:24.895 --> 00:18:28.067
A man this rich will buy for
a fellow outwater. I'm sure.

110
00:18:29.214 --> 00:18:30.377
One.

111
00:18:33.801 --> 00:18:37.007
That's an interesting
pair of boots you got.

112
00:18:37.851 --> 00:18:38.945
Trade?

113
00:18:39.023 --> 00:18:40.050
No.

114
00:18:40.128 --> 00:18:42.695
So. how long you
been out there. man?

115
00:18:46.823 --> 00:18:50.165
Don't hurt asking.
Talking costs you nothing.

116
00:18:57.702 --> 00:19:00.006
Depends.
What lunar is it?

117
00:19:00.515 --> 00:19:05.057
Well. let's see. Abbo.
Farch. June... It's August.

118
00:19:06.071 --> 00:19:07.770
It's August?
Yep.

119
00:19:09.520 --> 00:19:11.013
So. how long?

120
00:19:12.969 --> 00:19:14.233
Fifteen.

121
00:19:14.576 --> 00:19:16.138
Fifteen lunars?

122
00:19:22.442 --> 00:19:23.433
That's her.

123
00:19:23.715 --> 00:19:25.917
Enola.
Hey. what are you doing?

124
00:19:26.393 --> 00:19:27.589
No. you can't do that.

125
00:19:27.664 --> 00:19:30.231
I need another piece.
I want to draw some more.

126
00:19:30.310 --> 00:19:33.652
I'll give it to you.
Just stay in the back.

127
00:19:35.767 --> 00:19:38.470
With all those chits.
you could order up a bath.

128
00:19:38.545 --> 00:19:40.643
Have you ever had a freshwater
bath? Why are you talking to me?

129
00:19:40.720 --> 00:19:42.123
Just being friendly.

130
00:19:47.852 --> 00:19:49.790
Is that a tomato plant?

131
00:19:49.860 --> 00:19:50.954
Yeah.

132
00:19:51.032 --> 00:19:52.937
You have a keen eye.

133
00:19:53.007 --> 00:19:55.139
Saw one in a picture.
How much?

134
00:20:01.309 --> 00:20:02.802
Half your chits.

135
00:20:14.565 --> 00:20:15.761
I'll take them. too.

136
00:20:15.838 --> 00:20:16.932
Take what?

137
00:20:17.679 --> 00:20:19.413
You bought everything.

138
00:20:19.487 --> 00:20:20.890
I'll take them shelves.

139
00:20:23.103 --> 00:20:26.811
So. what did you see out there
in your 15 months?

140
00:20:26.885 --> 00:20:30.091
Such as?
An end to all this water.

141
00:20:30.165 --> 00:20:31.727
Asking the wrong person.

142
00:20:31.806 --> 00:20:33.070
Where did he come from?

143
00:20:33.146 --> 00:20:34.947
The one they buried today? Uh-huh.

144
00:20:35.019 --> 00:20:37.049
She found the
only end there is.

145
00:20:42.820 --> 00:20:44.792
I've got a proposition
for you. Mariner.

146
00:20:44.862 --> 00:20:45.922
I'm not bargaining.
I'm leaving.

147
00:20:46.000 --> 00:20:49.543
But you haven't even heard
anything yet. or seen it.

148
00:20:53.971 --> 00:20:57.582
You may have noticed us
burying a citizen today.

149
00:20:57.658 --> 00:20:59.876
That makes room for one more.

150
00:21:01.177 --> 00:21:02.534
I'm not staying.

151
00:21:02.607 --> 00:21:06.579
We're not asking you to.
All we want is your seed.

152
00:21:07.488 --> 00:21:10.499
We can look to
our own for impregnation.

153
00:21:10.577 --> 00:21:15.456
but too much of that sort
of thing gets undesirable.

154
00:21:16.190 --> 00:21:17.773
When she's pregnant.

155
00:21:17.850 --> 00:21:20.894
you go on your way with
all the supplies you need.

156
00:21:21.736 --> 00:21:24.917
You don't have anything.
You're dying.

157
00:21:29.972 --> 00:21:34.013
No man stays out that long
and turns down a woman.

158
00:21:35.286 --> 00:21:37.209
He's hiding something.

159
00:21:37.280 --> 00:21:39.633
Maybe he's a Smoker spy.

160
00:21:50.166 --> 00:21:54.242
When the elders say so. you
can leave. and not before.

161
00:22:14.011 --> 00:22:15.231
Gills.

162
00:22:17.000 --> 00:22:18.759
Mutation!

163
00:22:18.839 --> 00:22:21.273
He's a mutant!

164
00:22:22.943 --> 00:22:24.521
My hand!

165
00:22:31.112 --> 00:22:34.389
Don't let him
get in the water!

166
00:22:39.000 --> 00:22:40.325
Throw the nets!

167
00:23:05.781 --> 00:23:07.687
He's a murderer!

168
00:23:14.140 --> 00:23:15.359
By what right...

169
00:23:18.022 --> 00:23:20.102
You pay me
to keep the peace.

170
00:23:21.505 --> 00:23:23.053
This isn't it.
No!

171
00:23:23.131 --> 00:23:24.882
He has killed
one of ours.

172
00:23:24.956 --> 00:23:26.311
He was defending himself.

173
00:23:26.383 --> 00:23:27.840
He needs
to be destroyed!

174
00:23:27.909 --> 00:23:30.328
- Kill him. Let's kill him
- That may be.

175
00:23:30.398 --> 00:23:33.745
but not here
and not like this.

176
00:24:06.000 --> 00:24:07.230
What is it?

177
00:24:07.807 --> 00:24:09.108
Damn.

178
00:24:10.419 --> 00:24:13.626
They're too tight.
I can't get it off.

179
00:24:17.215 --> 00:24:18.743
Open the gate.

180
00:24:43.533 --> 00:24:46.203
This is another device
we found on the boat.

181
00:24:46.278 --> 00:24:50.489
A garrote cord.
for strangulation!

182
00:24:52.673 --> 00:24:55.114
We don't know what
this is all about.

183
00:24:55.184 --> 00:24:59.932
but we believe it to be some
sort of torturing device!

184
00:25:02.181 --> 00:25:03.446
And this...

185
00:25:03.521 --> 00:25:09.068
And this is a spy tool. for
listening to the unsuspecting.

186
00:25:12.494 --> 00:25:14.833
The evidence
speaks for itself.

187
00:25:15.808 --> 00:25:20.019
I move that we dispense with
the mute-o as soon as possible.

188
00:25:20.162 --> 00:25:22.364
and in no way...
Why?

189
00:25:24.582 --> 00:25:26.110
Why not use him?

190
00:25:26.188 --> 00:25:30.137
Because he is a threat to the
safety and the purity of this atoll.

191
00:25:30.206 --> 00:25:32.373
He is not a threat.
he's in a cage.

192
00:25:32.449 --> 00:25:34.788
He killed one
of ours. however.

193
00:25:36.567 --> 00:25:38.506
Is he dangerous or not?

194
00:25:39.213 --> 00:25:40.912
I'd say he is now.

195
00:25:41.590 --> 00:25:44.362
Well. but he came in
here with all this dirt.

196
00:25:44.436 --> 00:25:46.467
the likes of which
we haven't seen in years.

197
00:25:46.545 --> 00:25:47.775
not since Enola came.

198
00:25:47.851 --> 00:25:49.550
Oh. what about it?

199
00:25:50.998 --> 00:25:53.439
So it had to come
from somewhere.

200
00:25:55.150 --> 00:25:56.884
What if it came
from Dryland?

201
00:25:56.958 --> 00:25:58.520
Oh. don't start!

202
00:25:58.599 --> 00:26:00.538
He came from the west.
I can tell you that.

203
00:26:00.607 --> 00:26:04.349
Locusts come from there. I've
been told that. From the west.

204
00:26:04.425 --> 00:26:08.934
But if he is a spy.
this ichthyo-man

205
00:26:09.012 --> 00:26:11.384
will give away our
position. our weaknesses.

206
00:26:11.456 --> 00:26:12.859
And if he isn't?

207
00:26:12.929 --> 00:26:17.277
But he's still a mute-o. and he
can contaminate our community.

208
00:26:17.584 --> 00:26:19.557
And others!
What others?

209
00:26:19.860 --> 00:26:22.701
We haven't seen or heard from
another atoll in over a year.

210
00:26:22.773 --> 00:26:24.507
Let's keep to
the issue at hand.

211
00:26:24.581 --> 00:26:26.851
No. this is the
issue at hand.

212
00:26:26.924 --> 00:26:30.427
Every year. every month.
it gets worse.

213
00:26:30.809 --> 00:26:35.818
There are fewer atollers.
fewer traders. Dead gardens.

214
00:26:36.836 --> 00:26:39.403
these windmills
that don't work.

215
00:26:39.480 --> 00:26:41.956
desalinators that
can't be fixed.

216
00:26:43.465 --> 00:26:48.281
This place. this whole way
of living. it's ending.

217
00:26:49.793 --> 00:26:51.263
Doesn't anyone else
see that?

218
00:26:51.333 --> 00:26:53.739
When I was a boy. there
were lots of atolls.

219
00:26:53.810 --> 00:26:57.850
You keep on praying for help.
and now one man comes here

220
00:26:57.928 --> 00:26:59.867
who might actually be able
to save us... He's not a man!

221
00:26:59.939 --> 00:27:02.175
It doesn't matter what he is!

222
00:27:03.419 --> 00:27:08.201
I say. if he knows the way to
Dryland. make him show us where it is!

223
00:27:08.275 --> 00:27:11.584
People have looked for centuries.
and death is all they found!

224
00:27:11.656 --> 00:27:13.287
Well. at least
they died trying!

225
00:27:13.364 --> 00:27:16.307
It's a hoax. and the sooner
you realize that. Helen.

226
00:27:16.377 --> 00:27:18.544
the better off
we're all going to be!

227
00:27:18.620 --> 00:27:23.504
We'd be better off if we got
rid of that girl of hers. too!

228
00:27:23.643 --> 00:27:25.171
Right!
Yeah!

229
00:27:25.250 --> 00:27:28.890
The Smokers are looking for
her! I heard it from a trader!

230
00:27:31.812 --> 00:27:33.647
One matter at a time!

231
00:27:33.721 --> 00:27:36.790
I say get rid
of both of them!

232
00:27:37.839 --> 00:27:39.401
The mute-o and the girl!

233
00:27:39.480 --> 00:27:41.579
Yes! Yes!

234
00:27:44.000 --> 00:27:47.981
Order! Order!
Quiet down!

235
00:28:07.000 --> 00:28:09.259
You'd like this.
wouldn't you?

236
00:28:09.731 --> 00:28:11.025
Stick him.
Sure is quiet

237
00:28:11.098 --> 00:28:12.425
from the shark that
he was this afternoon.

238
00:28:12.496 --> 00:28:14.425
Maybe we hurt him.
Come on. let's go.

239
00:28:14.497 --> 00:28:16.552
No! Stick him again.

240
00:28:17.462 --> 00:28:19.221
I know you want it.

241
00:28:19.561 --> 00:28:21.991
I know. Maybe he don't
need his own kind.

242
00:28:41.921 --> 00:28:43.282
That's it!

243
00:28:46.387 --> 00:28:49.010
That's it!
Don't move. my dear!

244
00:28:49.086 --> 00:28:52.448
And from Aries to Taurus.
I forgot Taurus. the bull.

245
00:28:52.518 --> 00:28:56.004
and in the shoulder of the bull.
the Pleiades. the Six Sisters.

246
00:28:56.084 --> 00:28:58.604
Well. Seven Sisters.
but you can only see six.

247
00:28:58.683 --> 00:29:00.340
But at the beginning
of each lunar.

248
00:29:00.416 --> 00:29:03.437
one of the sisters is perpendicularly
lined up with Scorpius.

249
00:29:03.514 --> 00:29:05.909
And the Scorpius has a tail
just like the arrow.

250
00:29:05.981 --> 00:29:08.536
and that arrow bisects the circle.
like on the back of the child.

251
00:29:08.613 --> 00:29:10.872
Now. if I take into account
the seventh sister.

252
00:29:10.946 --> 00:29:12.672
and I give the
seventh sister a lunar.

253
00:29:12.745 --> 00:29:16.436
well. then that lunar. it will
run perpendicular to Scorpius.

254
00:29:16.511 --> 00:29:21.134
creating against the dawn horizon a
straight line that would run directly...

255
00:29:21.709 --> 00:29:23.400
Directly toward...

256
00:29:25.374 --> 00:29:26.633
Dryland!

257
00:29:28.407 --> 00:29:30.336
No.

258
00:29:32.505 --> 00:29:34.093
Is it a map?

259
00:29:35.704 --> 00:29:37.430
Is it a calendar?

260
00:29:41.468 --> 00:29:43.727
Is it symbols?
Is it language?

261
00:29:44.235 --> 00:29:46.392
You'd tell me if you knew.
wouldn't you. Enola?

262
00:29:46.468 --> 00:29:47.454
Mmm-hmm.

263
00:29:51.199 --> 00:29:52.890
What are you drawing?

264
00:29:52.965 --> 00:29:54.088
I don't know.

265
00:29:55.299 --> 00:29:59.388
Helen. look. Look at the
prodigal child's latest vision.

266
00:30:06.228 --> 00:30:08.453
We've got to get
out of here.

267
00:30:09.294 --> 00:30:10.882
I take it the meeting
didn't go well.

268
00:30:10.960 --> 00:30:12.651
They're putting us adrift.
Gregor. I can feel it.

269
00:30:12.726 --> 00:30:14.655
No. no. they're not
going to hurt you.

270
00:30:14.725 --> 00:30:17.314
I'd turn their lights
off if they did.

271
00:30:18.558 --> 00:30:21.044
How soon before
we can go?

272
00:30:21.123 --> 00:30:22.610
Another week. ideally.

273
00:30:23.123 --> 00:30:24.553
We don't have a week.

274
00:30:24.621 --> 00:30:27.812
Helen. I don't have any
idea yet where we can go.

275
00:30:29.587 --> 00:30:31.175
Try your books again.

276
00:30:31.253 --> 00:30:33.308
The books? There's...

277
00:30:33.452 --> 00:30:35.211
There's nothing in them.
There's nothing there.

278
00:30:35.286 --> 00:30:38.909
I've been through the books.
There's nothing in these books.

279
00:30:38.983 --> 00:30:42.345
She is the Annunciation.
I know it.

280
00:30:43.383 --> 00:30:45.279
I just don't know how.

281
00:30:46.948 --> 00:30:49.378
I'm a stupid man.
The answer's right there.

282
00:30:49.447 --> 00:30:52.410
It's just beyond me.

283
00:30:55.913 --> 00:30:57.536
Maybe he knows.

284
00:31:10.141 --> 00:31:13.627
Yes. I see.
They are webbed.

285
00:31:14.506 --> 00:31:18.697
One. two. three. four. five. six. seven.
eight. nine. ten digits. That's wonderful.

286
00:31:18.772 --> 00:31:22.258
They tell me. too. that you
have gills. Isotropic gills.

287
00:31:22.336 --> 00:31:25.299
Are they merely vestigial
or are they functional?

288
00:31:25.903 --> 00:31:29.764
My name is Gregor. I've just
come to pay you a little...

289
00:31:31.167 --> 00:31:32.290
Oh. my God.

290
00:31:34.999 --> 00:31:38.292
I'm sorry. I'm not laughing
at you. I'm excited.

291
00:31:38.366 --> 00:31:40.489
Your gills.
they're functional.

292
00:31:40.564 --> 00:31:43.959
Ichthyus sapien. You
can breathe in the water.

293
00:31:44.029 --> 00:31:45.822
How deep can you go?

294
00:31:45.896 --> 00:31:50.849
Look. I'm only here because I
want to learn more about you.

295
00:31:56.092 --> 00:31:59.055
You don't like humans
very much. do you?

296
00:32:00.124 --> 00:32:02.087
I can't say
that I blame you.

297
00:32:02.157 --> 00:32:05.519
But tell me. are all of your
kind as bad-tempered as you are?

298
00:32:09.388 --> 00:32:11.977
I have no kind.
Oh. fish rot.

299
00:32:12.053 --> 00:32:14.949
I'd be surprised if there weren't
others. and if there aren't.

300
00:32:15.020 --> 00:32:16.746
there will be eventually.

301
00:32:18.652 --> 00:32:21.979
Anyway. I've come here because
I need to ask you a question.

302
00:32:22.051 --> 00:32:26.276
Where did your dirt
come from?

303
00:32:26.349 --> 00:32:28.211
Is it from Dryland?

304
00:32:28.282 --> 00:32:30.507
Do you know what this is?

305
00:32:32.680 --> 00:32:35.075
The ancients. they did
something terrible. didn't they?

306
00:32:35.146 --> 00:32:38.906
To cause all this water.
Hundreds. hundreds of years ago.

307
00:32:38.979 --> 00:32:41.443
If I tell you.
will you open this lock?

308
00:32:44.311 --> 00:32:45.741
I haven't a key.

309
00:32:47.209 --> 00:32:48.968
There's a mooring cleat
down there.

310
00:32:49.041 --> 00:32:50.096
What?

311
00:32:50.176 --> 00:32:51.764
Good as any key.

312
00:32:51.841 --> 00:32:53.361
A mooring cleat?

313
00:32:55.074 --> 00:32:57.833
I won't hurt anyone.
I'll just leave.

314
00:32:59.373 --> 00:33:01.336
I'll be right back.

315
00:33:01.404 --> 00:33:02.629
Gregor!

316
00:33:03.037 --> 00:33:05.694
What's your business there?
Move along!

317
00:33:05.769 --> 00:33:07.063
I'm not a brave man.

318
00:33:07.536 --> 00:33:11.829
If you know anything about
Dryland. please tell me. Please!

319
00:33:12.934 --> 00:33:14.761
Don't let it die with you.

320
00:33:14.833 --> 00:33:17.353
No. no. no. no. Stop!

321
00:33:18.000 --> 00:33:20.978
Gregor!
Move along!

322
00:34:22.137 --> 00:34:23.574
Get out of the way!

323
00:34:29.841 --> 00:34:34.659
After considerable
deliberation of the evidence at hand.

324
00:34:35.767 --> 00:34:40.745
it is our decision that this mute-o
does. indeed. constitute a threat.

325
00:34:41.863 --> 00:34:45.001
Therefore. in the interest
of public safety.

326
00:34:45.079 --> 00:34:49.120
he is hereby sentenced
to be recycled

327
00:34:49.198 --> 00:34:51.229
in the customary fashion.

328
00:34:52.146 --> 00:34:53.411
Proceed.

329
00:35:03.400 --> 00:35:04.701
I'm sorry.

330
00:35:13.112 --> 00:35:17.427
Bones to berries.
Veins to vines.

331
00:35:17.802 --> 00:35:21.877
These tendons to trees.
This blood to brine.

332
00:35:21.954 --> 00:35:24.830
Too strange
for life he was.

333
00:35:24.902 --> 00:35:28.783
This mute-o
now does leave us.

334
00:35:28.854 --> 00:35:31.798
recycled and entombed.

335
00:35:32.270 --> 00:35:35.443
in the presence of him
who leads us.

336
00:35:45.500 --> 00:35:49.946
Smokers!
Get out of the sun!

337
00:35:53.720 --> 00:35:56.532
To your posts!

338
00:36:11.925 --> 00:36:14.089
Oh. my God!
Oh. my God!

339
00:36:29.485 --> 00:36:30.804
Kill!

340
00:36:30.878 --> 00:36:32.197
There!

341
00:36:42.563 --> 00:36:45.607
We are safe behind this wall.

342
00:36:46.943 --> 00:36:48.123
Aren't we?

343
00:36:57.643 --> 00:36:58.996
Let me out!

344
00:36:59.341 --> 00:37:00.960
Let me out! I'll fight!

345
00:37:20.163 --> 00:37:21.238
Help me!

346
00:37:21.316 --> 00:37:22.321
I can't find my dad!

347
00:37:22.404 --> 00:37:23.687
He's probably
on the wall.

348
00:37:23.763 --> 00:37:26.877
Now. go in there. get a weapon
and fight. Go! Go now. Go!

349
00:37:26.955 --> 00:37:27.960
Go. go!

350
00:37:32.933 --> 00:37:34.113
Come on. boys!

351
00:37:38.334 --> 00:37:40.672
I said move it!
Come on! Go! Go! Go!

352
00:37:45.637 --> 00:37:47.697
Give me the key
to the city now.

353
00:37:51.410 --> 00:37:53.713
Let's go! Let's go!
Let's go!

354
00:37:56.539 --> 00:37:59.757
Floor it! Floor it!
Come on!

355
00:38:21.741 --> 00:38:23.396
Swab it! Swab it!

356
00:38:25.172 --> 00:38:26.560
More ammo!

357
00:38:55.809 --> 00:38:57.707
Break down the door!

358
00:39:00.837 --> 00:39:02.225
My God!

359
00:39:11.841 --> 00:39:13.460
Go to work now!

360
00:39:14.084 --> 00:39:15.911
We'll have this atoll
in no time.

361
00:39:19.212 --> 00:39:21.410
Crank it! Crank it!

362
00:39:25.870 --> 00:39:27.118
Look!

363
00:39:46.725 --> 00:39:47.767
Look out!

364
00:40:23.000 --> 00:40:24.936
Oh. no!

365
00:40:48.873 --> 00:40:50.101
Oh. my...

366
00:40:53.387 --> 00:40:54.581
Helen!

367
00:40:56.997 --> 00:40:59.400
Keep that gas going!
Fill them up!

368
00:41:38.114 --> 00:41:40.175
It's the girl they want!

369
00:41:40.253 --> 00:41:42.416
Give them Enola
and they leave!

370
00:41:43.163 --> 00:41:46.467
Come quickly!
Helen! Helen!

371
00:42:21.505 --> 00:42:24.501
You're not supposed
to go yet!

372
00:42:24.581 --> 00:42:26.642
Infernal machine!

373
00:42:28.827 --> 00:42:30.626
Damn you!

374
00:42:39.021 --> 00:42:41.014
Infernal machine!

375
00:42:45.106 --> 00:42:47.703
Gregor. Gregor. wait!

376
00:42:47.780 --> 00:42:50.947
Helen. I tried. There was an accident.
I couldn't make it stop. Hurry!

377
00:42:51.023 --> 00:42:53.084
You can make it if you
try. Run! Please. stop!

378
00:42:53.162 --> 00:42:54.927
Up those stairs.
Run! Quickly!

379
00:42:55.001 --> 00:42:58.944
Wait! Wait! I'll throw
you a rope. Run quickly!

380
00:42:59.012 --> 00:43:00.640
Throw the rope now.
Run. Enola.

381
00:43:00.717 --> 00:43:02.379
Slow down! Wait!

382
00:43:02.455 --> 00:43:05.828
No! No!
Wait!

383
00:43:07.336 --> 00:43:09.363
Gregor. don't leave us! Oh. no!

384
00:43:09.442 --> 00:43:11.674
I'm sorry!
It was an accident!

385
00:43:16.161 --> 00:43:20.069
Helen! Enola!
Helen. I'm sorry!

386
00:43:40.264 --> 00:43:42.531
Shoot him. Shoot him.

387
00:44:09.514 --> 00:44:12.420
If I let you out of here.
you're taking us with you.

388
00:44:13.825 --> 00:44:14.986
Sure.

389
00:44:18.607 --> 00:44:20.577
Enola. get down.

390
00:44:21.715 --> 00:44:23.651
Here. Get over here.
Get down.

391
00:44:23.721 --> 00:44:25.452
Hurry! Come on!

392
00:44:29.070 --> 00:44:30.298
Get the gate.

393
00:45:29.743 --> 00:45:31.178
Hurry up!

394
00:45:31.247 --> 00:45:32.909
Kamikaze! Come on!

395
00:46:02.904 --> 00:46:04.497
That made a hole.

396
00:46:22.327 --> 00:46:24.663
Find her!
Get the girl!

397
00:46:29.981 --> 00:46:31.279
There!

398
00:46:38.973 --> 00:46:42.209
Go get that guy!
Go! Kill him!

399
00:46:46.830 --> 00:46:48.355
Wow!
Enola!

400
00:46:59.130 --> 00:47:02.194
You're too slow!
Run to the other side.

401
00:47:04.815 --> 00:47:05.976
Come on!

402
00:47:11.499 --> 00:47:14.233
Grab on!
Hold on. hold on.

403
00:47:18.419 --> 00:47:21.187
It's stuck!
I can't make it through!

404
00:47:21.261 --> 00:47:22.559
Let her go!

405
00:47:24.571 --> 00:47:25.972
Just drop her!

406
00:47:40.950 --> 00:47:43.684
Turn the wheel.
The wheel! Turn it!

407
00:47:48.505 --> 00:47:51.273
That! Come on! Push it!

408
00:47:51.347 --> 00:47:54.411
I am!
Hurry! Now pull!

409
00:47:54.490 --> 00:47:58.262
Push it! Push it hard!
Push it!

410
00:47:58.333 --> 00:48:01.830
Okay. okay! Now pull this!
Pull this! Go! Go!

411
00:48:01.910 --> 00:48:04.313
Pull it! Pull!

412
00:48:16.686 --> 00:48:18.154
Enola. jump.

413
00:48:20.130 --> 00:48:21.689
Jump! Look at me.
Jump! Now!

414
00:48:21.767 --> 00:48:22.995
Okay!

415
00:48:39.484 --> 00:48:41.751
Well. excuse me!

416
00:48:41.824 --> 00:48:45.025
Did I say anybody could leave
before the battle was over? Did I?

417
00:48:45.101 --> 00:48:46.159
No!
No!

418
00:48:46.236 --> 00:48:48.365
Well. do something.
I hate sails.

419
00:48:58.807 --> 00:49:01.301
Hey! Can you steer?

420
00:49:01.715 --> 00:49:03.308
Can I trust you?

421
00:49:38.185 --> 00:49:41.215
Answer me this. somebody.
Why is that boat still firing?

422
00:49:42.632 --> 00:49:45.297
What's that cousin's name?
Chuck.

423
00:49:45.373 --> 00:49:48.836
Hey. Chuck! He's pulling
him right into us.

424
00:49:49.617 --> 00:49:53.525
Maybe he doesn't answer to
Chuck. Call him Charles. Charles!

425
00:49:55.167 --> 00:49:58.403
Stop him! Stop him!

426
00:50:06.600 --> 00:50:08.035
Charles!

427
00:50:10.545 --> 00:50:11.570
Adios. cousins.

428
00:50:50.960 --> 00:50:54.491
Put me down!
Put me down!

429
00:51:05.000 --> 00:51:06.931
She's here somewhere.
Keep looking.

430
00:51:22.639 --> 00:51:28.265
Yes. I'II... 660 G's of hydro.
three-quarter grade or better.

431
00:51:28.341 --> 00:51:32.364
120 keys of assorted edibles.
jerk fish and plankton cakes.

432
00:51:32.442 --> 00:51:36.238
60 keys lamp oil.
44 old-growth grape vines.

433
00:51:36.310 --> 00:51:40.765
10 assorted fruit trees.
zero reloads.

434
00:51:40.844 --> 00:51:43.571
no animal storage
on this particular atoll.

435
00:51:43.644 --> 00:51:47.099
zero go-juice.
no refining capability.

436
00:51:47.179 --> 00:51:48.871
Primitive savages!

437
00:51:52.249 --> 00:51:54.214
How about smokes?

438
00:51:54.282 --> 00:51:55.940
Zero. Zero smokes.

439
00:51:57.349 --> 00:51:59.906
I remember when
this used to be fun.

440
00:52:00.550 --> 00:52:02.913
How long's it been since we
had a really good crusade?

441
00:52:02.984 --> 00:52:04.448
I know. I know.

442
00:52:04.518 --> 00:52:06.210
Tell me. how long?

443
00:52:06.552 --> 00:52:07.539
I don't know. I...

444
00:52:07.620 --> 00:52:12.280
Remember. there used to be
atolls on every horizon?

445
00:52:12.354 --> 00:52:13.579
Mmm-hmm.

446
00:52:14.421 --> 00:52:16.886
Where the hell
are they all going?

447
00:52:17.256 --> 00:52:19.050
Well. we sunk a few.

448
00:52:19.524 --> 00:52:20.921
Found this.

449
00:52:20.990 --> 00:52:22.114
Nord?

450
00:52:22.424 --> 00:52:26.481
Oh. now that's warmer. Hey.
all right. And the girl?

451
00:52:26.558 --> 00:52:28.921
She's not here.
She might have gotten away.

452
00:52:28.992 --> 00:52:30.456
That's why we came here!

453
00:52:30.527 --> 00:52:34.084
We didn't come here to
practice! We don't need practice!

454
00:52:36.529 --> 00:52:38.722
It's too late now!
Never mind!

455
00:52:39.929 --> 00:52:40.985
What you got?

456
00:52:41.064 --> 00:52:44.053
Couple of heartbeats over
there. Aren't saying much.

457
00:52:45.698 --> 00:52:49.653
If you'll notice the arterial nature of
the blood coming from the hole in my head.

458
00:52:49.733 --> 00:52:53.927
you can assume that we're
all having a real lousy day.

459
00:52:54.000 --> 00:52:57.459
So here it is. I need to
know about that tattooed girl.

460
00:52:59.000 --> 00:53:02.506
First one that
tells me lives.

461
00:53:02.610 --> 00:53:06.116
I saw a girl. I saw...

462
00:53:06.219 --> 00:53:09.576
It was... She had
a big tattoo on her.

463
00:53:10.122 --> 00:53:12.899
I saw a girl.

464
00:53:13.000 --> 00:53:17.653
I'm not sure. but I think she
got on that boat with three hulls.

465
00:53:18.702 --> 00:53:21.182
The boat that cost me
1.000 G's of go-juice?

466
00:53:21.250 --> 00:53:23.192
Yeah. the mute-o's boat.

467
00:53:23.700 --> 00:53:27.621
Mute-o?
Yeah. He got these slits here.

468
00:53:27.692 --> 00:53:30.800
Like fish gills.

469
00:53:30.878 --> 00:53:32.878
He wasn't really a man.

470
00:53:32.992 --> 00:53:36.307
A fluke of evolution.

471
00:53:37.351 --> 00:53:39.728
Oh. I'm sorry. A fluke of...

472
00:53:40.069 --> 00:53:42.480
Evolution.
I know!

473
00:53:42.551 --> 00:53:44.928
Let's have an intelligent
conversation here.

474
00:53:45.000 --> 00:53:47.648
I'll talk.
and you listen.

475
00:53:48.261 --> 00:53:53.031
In the beginning. the provider
said. "Let there be water."

476
00:53:53.104 --> 00:53:55.109
and the seas came forth.

477
00:53:56.064 --> 00:53:57.737
He created everything
that we know.

478
00:53:57.814 --> 00:53:59.761
Hey! Hey! Get in here!

479
00:53:59.832 --> 00:54:01.837
The sun. the air
that we breathe!

480
00:54:02.118 --> 00:54:08.402
He made. also. both man and
fish. and no combination thereof.

481
00:54:08.879 --> 00:54:12.708
He does not abide
the notion of evolution.

482
00:54:12.781 --> 00:54:14.419
Amen!
Amen!

483
00:54:14.968 --> 00:54:17.421
No! No. you said you
wouldn't kill me!

484
00:54:17.490 --> 00:54:20.274
Did I say that?
Witnesses. anybody. did I?

485
00:54:20.347 --> 00:54:21.756
Yes. yes. yes!
You said...

486
00:54:21.827 --> 00:54:23.832
You said it.
Oh. I may have.

487
00:54:26.267 --> 00:54:27.744
I may have.

488
00:54:29.194 --> 00:54:30.500
No. no. no. you said
you wouldn't...

489
00:54:34.844 --> 00:54:36.723
We get to the 'Deez.

490
00:54:38.175 --> 00:54:41.190
tank up that sky boat.
send it out on patrol.

491
00:54:42.646 --> 00:54:47.645
We gotta keep an eye out
for that ichthy-freak.

492
00:55:45.541 --> 00:55:47.488
I know what you're thinking.

493
00:55:47.559 --> 00:55:52.730
Thinking how much longer that hydro'd last
if there weren't three of us on this boat.

494
00:55:54.757 --> 00:55:57.003
Well. Enola won't drink much.

495
00:55:58.523 --> 00:56:00.058
And I won't...

496
00:56:01.214 --> 00:56:03.058
I won't drink at all.

497
00:56:04.140 --> 00:56:06.054
Not till we get there.

498
00:56:06.662 --> 00:56:07.968
Get where?

499
00:56:08.042 --> 00:56:10.586
I don't know.
wherever you're going.

500
00:56:12.044 --> 00:56:14.186
Wherever you got your dirt.

501
00:56:15.139 --> 00:56:18.934
Told you before. I salvaged it
off an atoll the Smokers hit.

502
00:56:20.216 --> 00:56:23.104
Smokers don't leave
anything after a raid.

503
00:56:23.816 --> 00:56:25.454
especially dirt.

504
00:56:27.112 --> 00:56:28.956
You been there. haven't you?

505
00:56:33.905 --> 00:56:35.279
Dryland?

506
00:56:36.630 --> 00:56:38.165
You know where it is.

507
00:56:39.791 --> 00:56:41.635
Yeah. I know where it is.

508
00:56:44.769 --> 00:56:47.726
And... And we're going?

509
00:56:48.603 --> 00:56:50.241
You and I are.

510
00:56:52.303 --> 00:56:54.583
The kid we gotta
pitch over the side.

511
00:56:57.482 --> 00:56:58.684
What?

512
00:56:58.761 --> 00:57:00.330
My boat's tore up.

513
00:57:01.553 --> 00:57:04.063
I'm taking on water.

514
00:57:04.142 --> 00:57:07.258
I'd be lucky to get half
a hydro ration out of that.

515
00:57:07.338 --> 00:57:10.765
You know...
I said I won't drink.

516
00:57:11.474 --> 00:57:12.710
For 12 days?

517
00:57:15.477 --> 00:57:20.384
No. It's better one of you dies
now than both of you die slow.

518
00:57:20.455 --> 00:57:21.725
Wait. Wait.

519
00:57:22.876 --> 00:57:25.959
We saved your life.
We got you out.

520
00:57:26.037 --> 00:57:29.556
No. you got me out so you
could get out. We're even.

521
00:57:29.636 --> 00:57:31.744
She can cook.
She can fish.

522
00:57:31.822 --> 00:57:34.102
So can I. Then take my
necklace. Take my necklace.

523
00:57:34.176 --> 00:57:36.456
I got better ones below.
No. look!

524
00:57:39.827 --> 00:57:42.577
After what you went through
back there on the atoll.

525
00:57:42.653 --> 00:57:45.003
I can understand
why you would want to.

526
00:57:45.813 --> 00:57:47.760
But she's a child.

527
00:57:59.066 --> 00:58:00.980
Is there something else.
then?

528
00:58:06.902 --> 00:58:08.644
Enola! Go below.

529
00:58:10.433 --> 00:58:11.635
Enola.

530
00:58:35.020 --> 00:58:36.188
Yeah.

531
00:58:36.937 --> 00:58:38.816
You said so yourself.

532
00:58:40.334 --> 00:58:42.144
Been out there a long time.

533
00:59:29.000 --> 00:59:31.937
Couple hours ago.
I was potential dirt to you.

534
00:59:32.274 --> 00:59:34.176
We're not like that.

535
00:59:34.246 --> 00:59:35.474
You all are.

536
00:59:41.296 --> 00:59:43.595
Know what I was
really thinking?

537
00:59:44.235 --> 00:59:47.331
Why I don't drop both of you
in my wake right now.

538
00:59:48.814 --> 00:59:50.578
You got nothing I need.

539
01:00:07.256 --> 01:00:09.384
You're taking us to Dryland.

540
01:00:14.305 --> 01:00:17.105
Killing's a hard thing
to do well.

541
01:00:17.178 --> 01:00:19.614
Believe me. I'm not
the one to start on.

542
01:00:19.684 --> 01:00:20.810
Both of us!

543
01:00:26.033 --> 01:00:28.434
How long you plan
to hold that on me?

544
01:00:28.504 --> 01:00:30.302
As long as it takes.

545
01:00:33.349 --> 01:00:34.816
Okay.

546
01:00:34.887 --> 01:00:35.912
No!

547
01:00:37.526 --> 01:00:39.860
Let me out of here!

548
01:00:40.733 --> 01:00:44.571
Where the hell are you?
Don't you touch my child.

549
01:00:45.044 --> 01:00:46.876
Come here!

550
01:00:53.463 --> 01:00:57.164
No. Don't hurt...

551
01:02:13.450 --> 01:02:16.319
Okay. now. don't move.
okay? There.

552
01:02:16.389 --> 01:02:19.657
Oh. looking real good. yeah.

553
01:02:19.731 --> 01:02:22.065
There. There.

554
01:02:22.136 --> 01:02:23.934
All done.

555
01:02:24.007 --> 01:02:27.537
Now. there may be some small
problem in depth perception.

556
01:02:27.615 --> 01:02:30.279
Well. it better not
screw up my short game.

557
01:02:32.459 --> 01:02:33.448
Well?

558
01:02:33.529 --> 01:02:35.191
Looks good.
I like it. Yeah.

559
01:02:35.266 --> 01:02:36.962
I like it better
than your real eye.

560
01:02:37.038 --> 01:02:38.199
Much better.

561
01:02:38.274 --> 01:02:40.744
What do you say. Toby?
The truth.

562
01:02:40.812 --> 01:02:42.110
Looks like slime.

563
01:02:42.182 --> 01:02:44.948
That's why I love children.
No guile.

564
01:02:48.966 --> 01:02:51.163
It does look like slime.

565
01:02:51.571 --> 01:02:53.870
And it feels like cold slime!

566
01:02:53.943 --> 01:02:56.539
Deacon?
What...

567
01:02:56.616 --> 01:02:59.143
I'm sorry. It's just that
there's a problem in the pit.

568
01:02:59.222 --> 01:03:00.815
Maybe you should come.

569
01:03:08.543 --> 01:03:09.908
Let's drive.

570
01:03:18.199 --> 01:03:21.034
The pit. Don't bother
with the scenic route.

571
01:03:21.106 --> 01:03:22.437
Drive!

572
01:03:24.180 --> 01:03:25.910
Hey. it's driving better.

573
01:03:38.814 --> 01:03:40.214
Get off!

574
01:03:41.721 --> 01:03:44.385
Get off.
Get out of the way.

575
01:03:44.461 --> 01:03:47.023
All right. all right.
all right. Okay. okay.

576
01:03:49.572 --> 01:03:53.171
Bless you. cousins. Bless you.
Bless all you cousins over there.

577
01:03:53.248 --> 01:03:54.510
Keep up the good work.

578
01:03:54.584 --> 01:03:57.613
Growth is progress.
Growth is progress.

579
01:03:57.692 --> 01:04:02.292
Somebody! Hey. up there!

580
01:04:02.369 --> 01:04:04.304
Take it off!

581
01:04:07.213 --> 01:04:10.048
Yes.
Your Deaconship.

582
01:04:10.119 --> 01:04:12.851
Hello. Good morning.

583
01:04:12.927 --> 01:04:16.560
Or night. whichever
the case may be.

584
01:04:16.635 --> 01:04:18.537
What is it? I'm a busy man.

585
01:04:18.607 --> 01:04:20.405
I thought you should know.

586
01:04:20.845 --> 01:04:25.411
We're down to exactly
four feet. nine inches

587
01:04:25.490 --> 01:04:27.220
of black stuff.

588
01:04:31.303 --> 01:04:32.770
Thank you. sir.

589
01:04:32.841 --> 01:04:34.605
How many G's
is that after refining?

590
01:04:34.678 --> 01:04:36.271
Maybe three refuelers.

591
01:04:36.348 --> 01:04:38.944
We'll burn through that
in two lunars. Sweet Joe!

592
01:04:39.021 --> 01:04:42.289
Will somebody please tell me
what's happening to this place?

593
01:04:43.131 --> 01:04:44.656
We outgrowed it.

594
01:04:45.569 --> 01:04:49.565
All right. the only thing that
is important is the tattooed girl.

595
01:04:49.645 --> 01:04:52.616
We don't spare any
go-juice finding her.

596
01:04:52.685 --> 01:04:54.152
We don't waste it
anywhere else.

597
01:04:54.222 --> 01:04:58.185
You cancel all those tractor pulls
and all that stuff until later.

598
01:04:58.265 --> 01:04:59.527
You got it?

599
01:05:01.306 --> 01:05:04.243
Dryland is the mother Iode.

600
01:05:05.449 --> 01:05:06.849
On your toes.

601
01:05:30.607 --> 01:05:32.769
Why don't you
use sea hydro?

602
01:05:34.082 --> 01:05:36.313
Salt's harder
on the filters.

603
01:05:58.939 --> 01:06:00.601
Can we have some?

604
01:06:04.019 --> 01:06:05.851
It's for her. not me.

605
01:06:17.048 --> 01:06:18.573
Here. come on.

606
01:06:19.889 --> 01:06:22.416
Is he going to take
use to Dryland?

607
01:06:22.595 --> 01:06:25.031
Sure he is. Yeah.

608
01:06:29.211 --> 01:06:31.578
All of it. All of it.
All of it.

609
01:06:33.855 --> 01:06:36.222
Good. Good. good.
Come on.

610
01:06:49.223 --> 01:06:51.283
Thanks for not killing us.

611
01:07:08.100 --> 01:07:10.368
Just stay away from him.

612
01:07:42.319 --> 01:07:44.450
Hi.
Move.

613
01:07:45.195 --> 01:07:47.634
Enola!
Enola. come here!

614
01:07:49.744 --> 01:07:51.007
Come on!

615
01:07:53.824 --> 01:07:55.921
Enola. come over here.

616
01:08:09.913 --> 01:08:11.176
Hey!

617
01:08:14.026 --> 01:08:15.586
What are you doing?

618
01:08:15.666 --> 01:08:18.504
Decorating your boat.
It's ugly.

619
01:08:22.255 --> 01:08:25.024
Where did you get this?
From down below.

620
01:08:25.099 --> 01:08:28.131
This is mine! You don't
touch anything of mine.

621
01:08:28.210 --> 01:08:29.372
I drew it for you.

622
01:08:29.446 --> 01:08:31.942
You don't draw on anything.
You understand?

623
01:08:41.288 --> 01:08:44.354
This is my boat.
I got it the way I like it.

624
01:08:44.967 --> 01:08:47.634
You take up space
and you slow me down.

625
01:08:51.221 --> 01:08:53.717
You know.
she's just a little girl.

626
01:08:53.797 --> 01:08:55.529
She doesn't know
your rules.

627
01:08:55.602 --> 01:08:56.934
You wanna stay?

628
01:08:57.142 --> 01:08:58.668
You teach her.

629
01:09:16.475 --> 01:09:18.504
Enola.
what'd I tell you?

630
01:09:24.000 --> 01:09:26.165
You're not so tough.
You know that?

631
01:09:30.724 --> 01:09:32.753
How many people
have you killed?

632
01:09:35.573 --> 01:09:38.445
Ten? Twenty?

633
01:09:40.358 --> 01:09:41.987
You talk a lot.

634
01:09:42.062 --> 01:09:44.296
I talk a lot 'cause
you don't talk at all.

635
01:09:45.040 --> 01:09:46.737
Now. how many?

636
01:09:48.853 --> 01:09:51.155
Including little girls?

637
01:09:51.227 --> 01:09:52.559
I'm not afraid of you.

638
01:09:56.413 --> 01:09:59.878
I told Helen you wouldn't be
so ugly if you cut your hair.

639
01:10:03.770 --> 01:10:05.604
In fact.
you talk all the time.

640
01:10:05.677 --> 01:10:08.014
It's like a storm when
you're around. HELEN: Enola!

641
01:10:08.086 --> 01:10:09.783
Hey! What are you doing?

642
01:10:10.661 --> 01:10:11.960
Helen!

643
01:10:12.032 --> 01:10:14.129
You butcher!
She can't swim!

644
01:10:14.474 --> 01:10:17.381
Help me! Helen!

645
01:10:18.654 --> 01:10:20.625
Helen. help me!

646
01:10:21.231 --> 01:10:22.632
Helen!

647
01:10:23.304 --> 01:10:25.401
Helen. help me!

648
01:10:33.741 --> 01:10:36.544
Helen! Helen!

649
01:10:36.616 --> 01:10:38.210
Hold on!

650
01:10:39.159 --> 01:10:40.388
Look at me. Look at me.
Look at me.

651
01:10:42.738 --> 01:10:46.683
Oh. please.
come back. Please!

652
01:10:46.751 --> 01:10:49.885
Please! Oh. please!

653
01:10:54.980 --> 01:10:56.175
Hey!

654
01:10:59.295 --> 01:11:01.996
Hold on. Okay. almost...

655
01:11:17.657 --> 01:11:21.898
Thanks. I swear. if you
ever touch her again...

656
01:11:22.607 --> 01:11:24.042
Look at me.

657
01:11:24.113 --> 01:11:26.678
You will go to bed that night
and you will never wake up.

658
01:11:26.755 --> 01:11:29.057
Shut up.
What?

659
01:11:30.000 --> 01:11:32.334
Smokers?
Yeah.

660
01:11:32.409 --> 01:11:34.743
Can't we outrun them?

661
01:11:37.126 --> 01:11:38.767
Not with my sail down.

662
01:11:57.438 --> 01:11:59.150
What are you
thinking about?

663
01:11:59.229 --> 01:12:00.976
That's a nice touch.

664
01:12:01.707 --> 01:12:03.113
That's them.

665
01:12:09.075 --> 01:12:10.892
Don't hit the kid.

666
01:12:25.530 --> 01:12:26.901
Hey!

667
01:12:32.931 --> 01:12:34.442
Coward!

668
01:12:43.190 --> 01:12:44.632
Oh. come on!

669
01:13:14.796 --> 01:13:15.815
No!

670
01:13:27.739 --> 01:13:28.758
Joe!

671
01:13:37.000 --> 01:13:38.253
Cut it!

672
01:13:47.299 --> 01:13:48.960
Come on! Come on!

673
01:14:21.165 --> 01:14:24.129
All right. Okay.

674
01:15:26.000 --> 01:15:28.481
Oh. I'm really sorry.

675
01:15:28.559 --> 01:15:31.946
I'm sorry. But you didn't
give me much choice.

676
01:15:32.017 --> 01:15:33.341
Oh. I know.

677
01:15:33.414 --> 01:15:37.130
But you ran away.
I... What?

678
01:15:37.204 --> 01:15:40.490
What are you...
No! Please. no! No!

679
01:15:50.271 --> 01:15:54.691
Don't ever touch anything
on my boat again.

680
01:15:58.450 --> 01:16:00.375
She said
she was sorry!

681
01:16:04.601 --> 01:16:07.387
That means you're supposed
to say something back!

682
01:16:29.835 --> 01:16:30.921
Did you say something?

683
01:16:31.000 --> 01:16:32.091
Mmm-mmm.

684
01:17:06.277 --> 01:17:07.402
Fore!

685
01:17:08.147 --> 01:17:09.374
Nice putt.

686
01:17:09.448 --> 01:17:13.885
It wasn't a putt. That was a drive.
And I wasn't even using my good eye.

687
01:17:14.055 --> 01:17:15.316
Damn it!

688
01:17:16.958 --> 01:17:18.925
You got an ashtray
or something?

689
01:17:19.527 --> 01:17:20.788
Oh. man.

690
01:17:22.332 --> 01:17:24.458
Damn thing never
did work right.

691
01:17:24.534 --> 01:17:26.899
You said to bring the pilot. Yes. I did.

692
01:17:26.971 --> 01:17:28.597
Well. he's here.

693
01:17:28.773 --> 01:17:31.002
Well. why didn't
you tell me?

694
01:17:31.710 --> 01:17:34.473
Come on. Nord.
Come on. tell me about it.

695
01:17:34.547 --> 01:17:36.173
The child. Did he have
the girl with him?

696
01:17:36.249 --> 01:17:39.081
Yeah. and some atoll witch!

697
01:17:40.889 --> 01:17:42.446
They killed Ed.

698
01:17:43.792 --> 01:17:45.952
Now. now. don't you
fret yourself.

699
01:17:46.028 --> 01:17:47.619
Plenty more where
Ed came from.

700
01:17:47.696 --> 01:17:49.629
Heading west-southwest?

701
01:17:49.699 --> 01:17:50.687
From here.

702
01:17:50.767 --> 01:17:54.726
Seems to me if we launch now. we
can cut him down just about here.

703
01:17:54.806 --> 01:17:58.070
If he doesn't change course.
It's not likely.

704
01:17:58.544 --> 01:18:01.034
He's a wily one.
that ichthy-demon.

705
01:19:44.644 --> 01:19:46.304
Hello!

706
01:19:48.149 --> 01:19:49.445
Drifter?

707
01:19:49.718 --> 01:19:50.706
Mmm-hmm.

708
01:19:50.786 --> 01:19:52.515
Are we gonna stop?

709
01:19:52.588 --> 01:19:54.521
Look at the flag!
His flag's up.

710
01:19:54.590 --> 01:19:57.058
I thought you all
stopped for each other.

711
01:20:01.566 --> 01:20:04.467
Well. maybe
he has some food!

712
01:20:07.707 --> 01:20:10.072
Don't find many who follow
the rules anymore.

713
01:20:10.143 --> 01:20:13.635
Well. make it quick.
What's your business?

714
01:20:18.821 --> 01:20:19.946
Trade.

715
01:20:22.659 --> 01:20:24.057
You got any resin?

716
01:20:27.566 --> 01:20:31.730
Resin? He's gotta be out of his mind. He's
out of his mind. I don't have any resin.

717
01:20:32.137 --> 01:20:34.661
You been outwater a long time.
haven't you?

718
01:20:35.676 --> 01:20:38.542
Must be joking me. man. Resin!
You don't got enough.

719
01:20:38.612 --> 01:20:40.341
How about food?

720
01:20:40.415 --> 01:20:42.382
Could you say that again.
please?

721
01:20:42.450 --> 01:20:44.417
How about food?

722
01:20:44.487 --> 01:20:47.887
Yeah. food.
Yeah. that'd be good. eh?

723
01:20:47.959 --> 01:20:50.893
I haven't eaten in.
well. you know. forever.

724
01:20:52.798 --> 01:20:56.461
Which one of you two is the cook?
'Cause I usually fall for the waitress.

725
01:20:58.704 --> 01:21:00.500
Like you said.
I don't have much.

726
01:21:00.574 --> 01:21:03.475
I'll say. Let's see.

727
01:21:03.945 --> 01:21:06.913
We can start with that wee
orchard you got over there.

728
01:21:09.819 --> 01:21:11.581
All right.
hold it there.

729
01:21:12.589 --> 01:21:14.613
We can talk.
Fair enough.

730
01:21:21.000 --> 01:21:23.263
It's a nice rod.
isn't it?

731
01:21:23.335 --> 01:21:25.530
I like that rod.
It's a nice rod.

732
01:21:32.780 --> 01:21:35.543
Got yourself a wee harem
going here. now. don't you. eh?

733
01:21:41.991 --> 01:21:43.957
What do you want
for the women?

734
01:21:44.028 --> 01:21:45.688
We're not for sale.

735
01:21:46.865 --> 01:21:49.594
Not for sale? There's no
such thing as not for sale.

736
01:21:49.668 --> 01:21:52.102
"Not for sale"!
Not for sale. eh?

737
01:21:53.306 --> 01:21:57.071
Are they a pair. or would you
consider selling them separate?

738
01:21:57.144 --> 01:21:59.076
No. Our business
is done here

739
01:21:59.146 --> 01:22:01.341
unless you got some resin
or sail you can part with.

740
01:22:01.416 --> 01:22:03.406
I told you once already.
I don't have any.

741
01:22:03.486 --> 01:22:05.885
I don't have.
Don't have. Don't have.

742
01:22:05.955 --> 01:22:10.084
Haven't seen either for trade in
lunars now. Wait. Wait. wait. wait.

743
01:22:13.464 --> 01:22:16.489
I do have something that'll
make you change your mind.

744
01:22:17.335 --> 01:22:19.632
Something that
you can't pass on.

745
01:22:21.974 --> 01:22:24.567
I took it off an
atoller refugee camp.

746
01:22:25.513 --> 01:22:27.845
The life savings
of the entire clan.

747
01:22:35.725 --> 01:22:38.693
Paper. Look at my wee paper.

748
01:22:39.095 --> 01:22:43.862
It's paper. Have you ever
seen paper? Look at it.

749
01:22:43.934 --> 01:22:45.230
Smell it.

750
01:22:47.673 --> 01:22:49.936
I been saving it
for a special trade.

751
01:22:52.946 --> 01:22:54.469
Don't you do it.

752
01:22:55.215 --> 01:22:58.149
You know. maybe I'm talking
to the wrong person here.

753
01:22:58.219 --> 01:23:01.051
Whose boat is this?
Is it your boat or your boat?

754
01:23:01.122 --> 01:23:04.181
No. No. it's his boat.
But he doesn't own us.

755
01:23:11.502 --> 01:23:12.865
Half an hour.

756
01:23:14.506 --> 01:23:16.996
Is he out of his mind
or something here?

757
01:23:17.075 --> 01:23:18.939
I got two pages in here. man!

758
01:23:19.011 --> 01:23:21.103
I mean. I'd get half a dozen
girls with this. you know.

759
01:23:21.180 --> 01:23:22.372
Half an hour.

760
01:23:24.017 --> 01:23:26.382
You trading or not?
Don't.

761
01:23:26.453 --> 01:23:27.544
Shut up.

762
01:23:29.490 --> 01:23:30.581
Okay.

763
01:23:33.194 --> 01:23:35.718
Forty-five minutes
with the wee one over there.

764
01:23:35.798 --> 01:23:38.266
I like to do the talking.
if you know what I mean.

765
01:23:39.468 --> 01:23:40.627
No!

766
01:23:42.772 --> 01:23:46.104
Fair enough.
Come. come. come. come. come!

767
01:23:46.677 --> 01:23:48.735
No. My boat.

768
01:23:50.616 --> 01:23:53.050
Fair enough. Fair enough.
Good. good. good. Aye.

769
01:23:53.119 --> 01:23:54.311
Helen.

770
01:23:54.387 --> 01:23:57.754
Sit down.
Enola. just do as he says.

771
01:24:27.728 --> 01:24:29.217
Half an hour.

772
01:24:34.102 --> 01:24:35.932
Come here. come here.

773
01:25:16.655 --> 01:25:18.554
It's been a while
for me now.

774
01:25:19.725 --> 01:25:22.750
Guess it's been more
than a while. actually.

775
01:25:26.233 --> 01:25:31.170
I've only got half an hour. Half an
hour. half an hour. half an hour...

776
01:25:32.574 --> 01:25:34.666
Right. right. right...

777
01:25:36.178 --> 01:25:39.237
You're so beautiful. Aye!
Anyone ever told you that?

778
01:25:40.116 --> 01:25:43.243
Give me that. What are you
doing? It's just a game.

779
01:25:45.823 --> 01:25:48.950
Oh. I... I...
We was just playing.

780
01:25:52.065 --> 01:25:54.089
The trade's off.

781
01:25:54.667 --> 01:25:56.531
I changed my mind.

782
01:25:56.936 --> 01:26:00.200
Well. you can't do that.

783
01:26:00.274 --> 01:26:02.673
I mean. a deal's a deal. aye?

784
01:26:03.345 --> 01:26:05.244
I just did.

785
01:26:05.447 --> 01:26:06.936
Hey!

786
01:26:07.416 --> 01:26:11.545
She's mine. Aye. No. No.
no. I won't have it. no.

787
01:26:11.621 --> 01:26:14.487
Go on. Get. get. get.
Go. go. go. Good. good.

788
01:26:14.558 --> 01:26:18.892
But don't go too far. now.
This won't take but a minute.

789
01:26:23.737 --> 01:26:28.435
I hate this boat.
I hate this boat!

790
01:26:29.443 --> 01:26:31.239
You garbage.

791
01:26:36.385 --> 01:26:41.288
You're pretty stingy for a man who's
got everything. aren't you. now?

792
01:26:57.845 --> 01:26:59.071
You...

793
01:27:11.327 --> 01:27:13.021
Where's me boat?

794
01:27:14.465 --> 01:27:15.828
Where's me boat?

795
01:27:23.776 --> 01:27:25.241
Help me to me boat.

796
01:27:28.648 --> 01:27:29.874
Me boat.

797
01:28:05.661 --> 01:28:08.060
Yeah. if he knows
he's been spotted.

798
01:28:08.264 --> 01:28:12.165
he'll expect us to expect
him to change course.

799
01:28:12.235 --> 01:28:15.761
which is exactly why
he'll keep his heading.

800
01:28:15.840 --> 01:28:19.070
The important question is.
where's he heading?

801
01:28:19.144 --> 01:28:22.602
And does he know
how precious his cargo is?

802
01:28:22.682 --> 01:28:25.707
Dryland. Salvation.

803
01:28:26.319 --> 01:28:30.448
Room to grow. Eighteen holes.
Thirty-six. Seventy-two!

804
01:28:32.159 --> 01:28:35.526
I say that he's headed here.
and we take him here.

805
01:29:02.963 --> 01:29:05.397
How long before
we get some wind?

806
01:29:07.136 --> 01:29:08.568
Days. maybe.

807
01:29:09.705 --> 01:29:11.637
Then why don't we fish?

808
01:29:12.043 --> 01:29:13.339
What for?

809
01:29:14.011 --> 01:29:16.240
So we can get
something to eat?

810
01:29:16.313 --> 01:29:18.109
We ate two days ago.

811
01:29:18.249 --> 01:29:19.509
You ate!

812
01:29:22.488 --> 01:29:23.714
Just...

813
01:29:26.661 --> 01:29:28.560
Just help me fix this.

814
01:29:29.963 --> 01:29:32.123
I'll catch
something myself.

815
01:29:32.333 --> 01:29:35.928
You're not going to catch
anything with this around here.

816
01:29:37.506 --> 01:29:41.373
Look. we're not trying
to make you angry.

817
01:29:45.115 --> 01:29:47.480
And you don't disappear just
because you turn your back on us.

818
01:29:47.551 --> 01:29:49.483
You don't know what
fishing's like around here.

819
01:29:49.554 --> 01:29:52.646
Well. then you do it.
if you're the authority.

820
01:30:03.271 --> 01:30:05.739
Maybe he doesn't
know how to fish.

821
01:30:07.876 --> 01:30:09.035
I think
you're right. Enola.

822
01:30:09.111 --> 01:30:10.805
Shut up. will you?

823
01:30:11.381 --> 01:30:13.280
I'm trying to listen
for engines.

824
01:30:13.350 --> 01:30:17.251
I will not shut up until
you stop what you're doing

825
01:30:17.321 --> 01:30:20.585
and you help me find something
to eat for this child!

826
01:30:20.660 --> 01:30:23.287
I will scream
so loud that...

827
01:30:24.963 --> 01:30:26.520
What the... No!

828
01:30:28.502 --> 01:30:31.299
Never catch anything
with this. It's useless.

829
01:30:37.078 --> 01:30:41.776
Look. I'm sorry.
You were right about the pole.

830
01:30:42.719 --> 01:30:45.380
You were right.
but we have to eat.

831
01:30:50.628 --> 01:30:52.618
Now. I know you can hear me!

832
01:30:52.698 --> 01:30:56.224
Now. we can fish for ourselves.
You show us what to do.

833
01:30:56.535 --> 01:30:58.934
You must know how.
Even you gotta eat!

834
01:30:59.005 --> 01:31:00.470
You just sit there.

835
01:31:24.537 --> 01:31:26.060
What...

836
01:31:26.138 --> 01:31:27.364
I don't know.

837
01:32:03.651 --> 01:32:05.242
Happy now?

838
01:32:23.675 --> 01:32:25.801
You don't like
my singing. do you?

839
01:32:29.149 --> 01:32:32.584
Helen says you don't like my
singing 'cause you can't sing.

840
01:32:40.764 --> 01:32:43.061
Ever try and listen?
To what?

841
01:32:46.204 --> 01:32:48.068
The sound of the world.

842
01:32:52.878 --> 01:32:55.970
I don't hear anything.
That's because you're too loud

843
01:32:56.049 --> 01:32:58.039
and you're moving
around all the time.

844
01:32:58.118 --> 01:32:59.778
Try sitting still.

845
01:33:01.589 --> 01:33:03.054
Eyeball?

846
01:33:20.979 --> 01:33:23.378
Go ahead.
drink all you want.

847
01:33:24.684 --> 01:33:26.674
It's gonna rain tonight.

848
01:33:45.875 --> 01:33:48.001
I wish I had feet like his.

849
01:33:50.282 --> 01:33:52.078
Then maybe I could swim.

850
01:33:52.150 --> 01:33:53.615
Enola.

851
01:33:58.759 --> 01:34:00.019
Sorry.

852
01:34:04.499 --> 01:34:06.967
Never met a person
who couldn't swim before.

853
01:34:09.605 --> 01:34:10.901
I can't.

854
01:34:13.643 --> 01:34:15.542
People said I was weird.

855
01:34:16.581 --> 01:34:18.513
Maybe they were right.

856
01:34:21.486 --> 01:34:23.749
Maybe they were right
about you. too.

857
01:35:28.101 --> 01:35:29.931
Is that from Dryland?

858
01:35:33.407 --> 01:35:34.532
Yeah.

859
01:35:47.091 --> 01:35:49.581
You know. I don't even
know your name.

860
01:35:49.660 --> 01:35:51.320
I don't need one.

861
01:35:53.198 --> 01:35:55.632
Enola wanted to
give this to you.

862
01:35:59.506 --> 01:36:00.802
And this.

863
01:36:04.478 --> 01:36:06.468
She won't take it again.

864
01:36:12.688 --> 01:36:14.917
You don't look
much like her.

865
01:36:15.726 --> 01:36:18.455
Well. I'm not her mother.
if that's what you're asking.

866
01:36:18.530 --> 01:36:20.156
You act like it.

867
01:36:20.799 --> 01:36:27.261
About six years ago. this basket
floated into the atoll with Enola in it.

868
01:36:28.942 --> 01:36:33.470
Of course. everyone wanted to shove
her back out to sea. That was the law.

869
01:36:33.748 --> 01:36:35.544
She was so precious.

870
01:36:36.584 --> 01:36:38.414
I wanted to keep her.

871
01:36:39.354 --> 01:36:43.084
So the elders talked and said
that if I wanted her so badly

872
01:36:43.326 --> 01:36:46.192
that I could never
have a child of my own.

873
01:36:48.266 --> 01:36:51.724
There was no one else. She
would have died otherwise.

874
01:36:51.870 --> 01:36:53.130
So?

875
01:36:53.205 --> 01:36:55.137
It's called compassion.

876
01:36:58.744 --> 01:37:02.680
You probably wouldn't understand.
after being alone so much.

877
01:37:02.884 --> 01:37:04.407
I'm not alone.

878
01:37:05.320 --> 01:37:07.412
Got this boat for a friend.

879
01:37:08.757 --> 01:37:12.590
It don't lie to me. don't
cut my throat when I'm asleep.

880
01:37:14.197 --> 01:37:16.187
Gives me a place to be.

881
01:37:16.600 --> 01:37:18.362
I pity you. really.

882
01:37:19.671 --> 01:37:21.637
What's pity?
You don't know?

883
01:37:22.507 --> 01:37:24.565
If I knew.
I wouldn't ask.

884
01:37:25.777 --> 01:37:29.507
Well. if you don't know. I
could never make you understand.

885
01:37:32.653 --> 01:37:34.677
What are those
marks on her back?

886
01:37:34.756 --> 01:37:37.848
Nothing. They're just
fanciful things.

887
01:37:38.927 --> 01:37:40.587
Like what she draws?

888
01:37:40.662 --> 01:37:42.628
She draws what she sees.

889
01:37:43.133 --> 01:37:44.929
She's like a mirror.

890
01:37:46.003 --> 01:37:48.766
People on the atoll
thought she was a...

891
01:37:50.174 --> 01:37:51.366
Freak?

892
01:37:54.013 --> 01:37:55.104
Yeah.

893
01:37:55.180 --> 01:37:57.512
I just thought
she was special.

894
01:38:05.693 --> 01:38:08.661
I'm not giving it to her.
It's just...

895
01:38:09.064 --> 01:38:10.256
A loan.

896
01:38:11.301 --> 01:38:13.791
Yeah. I'm not
giving it to her.

897
01:38:19.610 --> 01:38:21.440
Is Dryland beautiful?

898
01:38:24.050 --> 01:38:25.448
You'll see.

899
01:39:39.409 --> 01:39:40.534
Enola?

900
01:39:41.778 --> 01:39:44.143
Enola. what are you doing?

901
01:39:44.213 --> 01:39:46.271
Those monsters'll
kill her!

902
01:39:46.350 --> 01:39:47.748
No. they're asleep now.

903
01:39:50.788 --> 01:39:52.311
Hands around my neck.

904
01:39:54.427 --> 01:39:57.259
Let the water tell your
arms and legs how to move.

905
01:39:57.730 --> 01:40:00.027
We're going down.
Hold your breath.

906
01:41:38.986 --> 01:41:40.976
What is it?

907
01:41:41.056 --> 01:41:42.647
What is it?

908
01:41:43.959 --> 01:41:46.051
Barter outpost.

909
01:41:46.462 --> 01:41:48.588
You said we'd
get to Dryland today.

910
01:41:49.000 --> 01:41:51.946
Today. Tomorrow.
What's it matter?

911
01:41:53.356 --> 01:41:54.886
I need resin.

912
01:42:05.053 --> 01:42:06.454
What is that?

913
01:42:06.529 --> 01:42:07.825
It's PortuGreek.

914
01:42:09.720 --> 01:42:11.250
Their own language.

915
01:42:14.042 --> 01:42:16.122
Or so I thought.

916
01:42:42.927 --> 01:42:46.282
There's my girl. Yeah.

917
01:42:47.111 --> 01:42:49.846
Howdy. darling.
Come on in here now.

918
01:43:20.147 --> 01:43:21.924
What's going on?

919
01:43:22.000 --> 01:43:23.218
Smokers.

920
01:43:26.375 --> 01:43:27.989
What the hell?

921
01:43:31.611 --> 01:43:34.682
He's spotted us. Sound it!

922
01:43:34.758 --> 01:43:38.667
Sound it! Sound it!
Sound it! Sound it!

923
01:43:59.681 --> 01:44:00.968
Enola!

924
01:44:14.000 --> 01:44:15.998
Starboard side! Now!

925
01:44:17.652 --> 01:44:19.090
Get in the chair!

926
01:44:25.492 --> 01:44:27.228
Watch it.
He's clearing the net.

927
01:44:40.202 --> 01:44:41.297
Go to the helm.

928
01:44:44.425 --> 01:44:46.491
Get the centerboard!
Centerboard?

929
01:44:46.570 --> 01:44:50.351
What centerboard? Where.
exactly? I don't know what to do!

930
01:44:50.658 --> 01:44:53.032
Under the helm!
Pull the handle!

931
01:44:55.617 --> 01:44:57.146
Hurry! Hurry!

932
01:45:00.073 --> 01:45:02.105
It's too late. Over here!

933
01:45:21.486 --> 01:45:22.514
No!

934
01:45:40.117 --> 01:45:41.646
Give me that rifle.

935
01:45:42.396 --> 01:45:47.079
Boy. if you wanna do something
right. you've got to do it yourself.

936
01:45:47.723 --> 01:45:49.194
All right.

937
01:45:56.402 --> 01:45:57.704
I winged him.

938
01:45:57.775 --> 01:46:01.315
I say we load all the go-juice onto
one boat and run the freak down.

939
01:46:01.395 --> 01:46:05.004
You can't catch him in ten boats.
and you wanna send just one?

940
01:46:05.081 --> 01:46:07.650
Well. I pray that
you're joking.

941
01:46:15.838 --> 01:46:17.574
Bring me the trackers.

942
01:46:31.653 --> 01:46:33.216
You lied to us.

943
01:46:34.333 --> 01:46:36.468
You were gonna
sell us back there!

944
01:46:36.544 --> 01:46:38.039
We both lied.

945
01:46:38.287 --> 01:46:39.416
What?

946
01:46:41.337 --> 01:46:42.706
I saw what I saw.

947
01:46:42.779 --> 01:46:43.976
He's hurt.

948
01:46:44.051 --> 01:46:47.123
Well. he should be.
He was gonna sell us.

949
01:46:52.328 --> 01:46:54.600
No wonder you
let her keep it!

950
01:46:55.075 --> 01:46:56.741
No. you leave it.

951
01:46:58.191 --> 01:47:00.028
Why do they want her?

952
01:47:00.940 --> 01:47:03.474
You know. there's nothing
human about you.

953
01:47:03.554 --> 01:47:05.928
They should have killed you
the day you were born.

954
01:47:06.000 --> 01:47:07.395
They tried.

955
01:47:10.360 --> 01:47:11.879
No more lies.

956
01:47:14.454 --> 01:47:16.507
What are the marks
on her back?

957
01:47:16.951 --> 01:47:20.173
People say
it's the way to Dryland.

958
01:47:20.247 --> 01:47:21.902
Dryland's a myth!

959
01:47:21.978 --> 01:47:24.871
No! You said so yourself
that you know where it is.

960
01:47:25.572 --> 01:47:26.728
You did.

961
01:47:31.831 --> 01:47:35.222
You're a fool to believe in
something you've never seen before.

962
01:47:35.293 --> 01:47:39.446
I've seen it. I've touched it! Dirt
that was richer and darker than yours.

963
01:47:39.521 --> 01:47:41.506
It was in the basket
we found Enola in!

964
01:47:41.585 --> 01:47:44.171
It doesn't exist! Well.
how can you be so sure?

965
01:47:44.247 --> 01:47:49.069
Because I've sailed farther than most
have dreamed. and I've never seen it.

966
01:47:50.705 --> 01:47:52.666
But the things on your boat!

967
01:47:53.601 --> 01:47:56.028
"Things on my boat" what?

968
01:47:56.099 --> 01:47:59.525
There are things on your boat
that nobody has ever seen!

969
01:47:59.593 --> 01:48:01.816
What are these shells?

970
01:48:01.889 --> 01:48:04.849
And that
reflecting glass?

971
01:48:04.920 --> 01:48:08.210
And the music box? That...

972
01:48:09.479 --> 01:48:12.837
Well. if not from Dryland.
then where? Where?

973
01:48:15.871 --> 01:48:17.526
You wanna see Dryland?

974
01:48:19.466 --> 01:48:21.393
You really wanna see it?

975
01:48:23.128 --> 01:48:25.181
I'll take you to Dryland.

976
01:48:39.006 --> 01:48:40.366
Get in.

977
01:48:46.597 --> 01:48:48.082
Well. what about Enola?

978
01:48:48.160 --> 01:48:49.782
There's only air for one.

979
01:48:49.858 --> 01:48:52.149
Get in the water.
It'll be all right.

980
01:49:04.738 --> 01:49:06.427
Don't touch anything.

981
01:49:11.463 --> 01:49:12.892
Okay?

982
01:52:49.000 --> 01:52:50.467
I didn't know.

983
01:52:52.642 --> 01:52:54.406
All this time...

984
01:52:55.984 --> 01:52:57.816
I didn't know.

985
01:52:57.889 --> 01:52:59.414
Nobody does.

986
01:53:07.814 --> 01:53:09.783
Can you get us
out of here?

987
01:53:09.853 --> 01:53:13.349
I'd say there're
two chances of that.

988
01:53:13.661 --> 01:53:16.098
Hey!
No way and no how.

989
01:53:16.871 --> 01:53:19.900
Should've bought me
that drink. Come on!

990
01:53:19.978 --> 01:53:21.537
This way. Come on!

991
01:53:28.767 --> 01:53:30.896
Proper introductions first.

992
01:53:31.875 --> 01:53:33.342
I'm the Deacon.

993
01:53:38.659 --> 01:53:43.295
If you don't recall the face. perhaps
it's 'cause I didn't always look like this.

994
01:53:46.513 --> 01:53:50.887
Now. I suspect
she's somewhere real close.

995
01:53:51.124 --> 01:53:53.424
So we can tear this boat
apart looking for her.

996
01:53:53.497 --> 01:53:56.162
but I'd rather somebody
tell me where she is.

997
01:53:56.237 --> 01:53:58.970
And the first one
that does that lives.

998
01:53:59.044 --> 01:54:03.885
And the runner-up... Well.
actually. there are no runners-up.

999
01:54:06.396 --> 01:54:08.594
Oh. sweet Joe.
I love this part.

1000
01:54:08.669 --> 01:54:11.732
Choose them.
One. two. Live or die.

1001
01:54:13.180 --> 01:54:15.275
You know. personally.

1002
01:54:16.490 --> 01:54:19.428
I'd rather shoot the
sperm-of-the-devil here.

1003
01:54:21.000 --> 01:54:22.814
But you know something?

1004
01:54:22.888 --> 01:54:25.404
I don't think you're
gonna tell me. are you?

1005
01:54:26.226 --> 01:54:28.271
Too bad.

1006
01:54:28.518 --> 01:54:31.850
Come on. What do you say?

1007
01:54:31.923 --> 01:54:34.002
She's not your kind.

1008
01:54:35.497 --> 01:54:37.852
You don't even have a kind.

1009
01:54:37.925 --> 01:54:41.693
If you say it.
he'll still kill us both.

1010
01:54:46.522 --> 01:54:48.635
Let's not get ahead
of ourselves.

1011
01:54:50.533 --> 01:54:52.452
If you don't tell me.

1012
01:54:52.522 --> 01:54:55.544
I swear to Poseidon
I will torch your boat.

1013
01:55:02.604 --> 01:55:05.465
Refresh my memory. What
happens when neither of them talks?

1014
01:55:05.537 --> 01:55:07.892
Never happened before.
Never happened before.

1015
01:55:09.785 --> 01:55:11.128
All right!

1016
01:55:11.200 --> 01:55:13.888
If they won't tell us
where she is. do them!

1017
01:55:13.964 --> 01:55:16.353
Both of them!
Kill them now!

1018
01:55:16.426 --> 01:55:17.769
No!

1019
01:55:18.213 --> 01:55:19.247
No!

1020
01:55:19.325 --> 01:55:21.875
So gullible!
Bring her here.

1021
01:55:23.945 --> 01:55:26.806
Take and ye shall receive!
No! Leave her!

1022
01:55:26.877 --> 01:55:29.335
So ends your daily sermonette!

1023
01:55:30.553 --> 01:55:33.988
Yes! Yes! Yes!

1024
01:55:35.408 --> 01:55:38.165
Here. take them. boys.
Take care of her.

1025
01:55:39.992 --> 01:55:41.404
What is it?

1026
01:55:43.499 --> 01:55:44.809
Stunning.

1027
01:55:45.386 --> 01:55:47.971
I don't have words
to even begin to...

1028
01:55:48.049 --> 01:55:49.726
It's magnificent!

1029
01:55:50.005 --> 01:55:51.509
Look at that!

1030
01:55:51.757 --> 01:55:53.640
That's square footage!

1031
01:55:55.568 --> 01:55:59.003
All we gotta do is figure out
this map. Turn her upside down.

1032
01:55:59.074 --> 01:56:00.785
Does that mean
anything to you?

1033
01:56:00.861 --> 01:56:02.572
No.

1034
01:56:02.649 --> 01:56:04.866
We'll figure it out back at
the 'Deez. Back at the 'Deez. boys.

1035
01:56:04.941 --> 01:56:07.330
Careful with her.
Careful with her!

1036
01:56:07.401 --> 01:56:09.687
What about them?
Do them both.

1037
01:56:10.403 --> 01:56:11.676
Torch the boat.

1038
01:56:15.426 --> 01:56:17.033
We have to go under!

1039
01:56:19.167 --> 01:56:21.177
No. I can't
breathe like you!

1040
01:56:22.000 --> 01:56:23.832
I'll breathe
for both of us.

1041
01:56:50.507 --> 01:56:51.941
Helen!

1042
01:56:54.551 --> 01:56:56.486
Helen. help!

1043
01:56:56.556 --> 01:57:00.122
Helen! Helen!

1044
01:57:47.422 --> 01:57:48.913
My boat.

1045
01:57:58.886 --> 01:58:00.251
Enola.

1046
01:58:09.214 --> 01:58:10.579
All right!

1047
01:58:10.650 --> 01:58:13.247
I can't wait to get this
thing out on some pavement.

1048
01:58:13.325 --> 01:58:15.990
Build some highways
and some freeways.

1049
01:58:16.232 --> 01:58:17.860
There you go. cous.
There you go. cous.

1050
01:58:17.935 --> 01:58:20.167
Be careful. now. You break
them. you can't use them.

1051
01:58:20.242 --> 01:58:21.676
Come on!

1052
01:58:21.746 --> 01:58:23.442
What's happening. cousin?

1053
01:58:23.516 --> 01:58:26.580
Not a word. She just
sits there and leaks.

1054
01:58:26.659 --> 01:58:30.259
Well. shiver to the liver. This'll
make her give up all her secrets. huh?

1055
01:58:30.334 --> 01:58:31.768
Yeah. or kill her.

1056
01:58:31.839 --> 01:58:35.074
Let me talk to her first.
I'm real good with kids.

1057
01:58:38.088 --> 01:58:41.185
What is this?
Get those chains off her.

1058
01:58:41.263 --> 01:58:44.168
What are we.
barbarians here?

1059
01:58:44.238 --> 01:58:46.640
Goodness gracious.
Sakes alive.

1060
01:58:46.711 --> 01:58:49.512
Come on. out of here.
you big. nasty animal. you!

1061
01:58:50.889 --> 01:58:52.756
Well. rub-a-dub-dub.

1062
01:58:55.000 --> 01:59:02.979
You wanna come over here
and sit on my lap?

1063
01:59:12.000 --> 01:59:15.652
No. Well. I got something
right here I know you'd like.

1064
01:59:17.129 --> 01:59:18.954
Like to draw. don't you?

1065
01:59:23.369 --> 01:59:24.893
Now. they're yours.

1066
01:59:26.178 --> 01:59:30.488
if you help me with just
one problem. all right?

1067
01:59:32.908 --> 01:59:34.800
Now. I got this parish.

1068
01:59:35.783 --> 01:59:38.288
Good parish. Large parish.

1069
01:59:39.997 --> 01:59:42.569
Getting larger
all the time. in fact.

1070
01:59:43.134 --> 01:59:47.243
Now. you know. I just
don't have enough faith

1071
01:59:49.015 --> 01:59:50.417
for all these people.

1072
01:59:50.485 --> 01:59:52.767
Why don't you
make less people?

1073
01:59:53.000 --> 01:59:54.232
Pardon?

1074
01:59:54.877 --> 01:59:58.660
The atoll. babies are born
only when there's room.

1075
01:59:59.169 --> 02:00:02.209
That way. there's food
and hydro for everyone.

1076
02:00:03.193 --> 02:00:06.198
Well. that's
a quaint suggestion.

1077
02:00:07.350 --> 02:00:09.623
But it don't
really play here.

1078
02:00:09.866 --> 02:00:13.981
considering we are. in fact.
the Church of Eternal Growth.

1079
02:00:15.566 --> 02:00:20.789
See. what we need is
more land. for more people.

1080
02:00:20.864 --> 02:00:24.475
Now. that tattoo
on your back.

1081
02:00:24.552 --> 02:00:29.478
I've been told that
that's actually a map?

1082
02:00:32.029 --> 02:00:34.302
It's the way to Dryland.

1083
02:00:34.377 --> 02:00:36.215
Now we're getting someplace.

1084
02:00:38.366 --> 02:00:41.577
Could you teach me
how to read that?

1085
02:00:44.000 --> 02:00:46.917
Setback.

1086
02:00:48.000 --> 02:00:52.912
Well. have you ever heard any
of your friends talk about it?

1087
02:00:53.000 --> 02:00:56.744
You know. like your mommy
or your pet fish?

1088
02:00:56.822 --> 02:00:58.358
Did he say anything?

1089
02:00:58.439 --> 02:01:01.008
You shouldn't make fun of
him. He wouldn't like it.

1090
02:01:01.092 --> 02:01:03.285
He took out my eye.

1091
02:01:03.365 --> 02:01:04.901
And if I ever see him again.

1092
02:01:04.982 --> 02:01:09.489
I'm gonna cut open his head
and eat his brains!

1093
02:01:09.563 --> 02:01:11.863
You think he'd like that?

1094
02:01:11.938 --> 02:01:15.928
Can't kill him. He's
even meaner than you are.

1095
02:01:16.759 --> 02:01:19.094
But he's not here.

1096
02:01:19.168 --> 02:01:21.221
And he ain't coming.

1097
02:01:21.304 --> 02:01:23.497
And no one's gonna save you.

1098
02:01:24.747 --> 02:01:26.741
He'll come for me.
He will.

1099
02:01:26.814 --> 02:01:29.418
Then you better tell me
what I wanna know

1100
02:01:29.499 --> 02:01:33.102
or he can see what's
left of you in a jar.

1101
02:01:36.386 --> 02:01:39.026
Now. I'm glad
we had this little talk.

1102
02:01:40.311 --> 02:01:41.683
Chain her.

1103
02:01:44.271 --> 02:01:45.807
Chain her up.

1104
02:01:46.957 --> 02:01:50.114
He'll come for me!
He'll take me away!

1105
02:02:02.349 --> 02:02:04.542
We're going to die here.
aren't we?

1106
02:02:25.281 --> 02:02:26.581
Aren't we?

1107
02:02:36.851 --> 02:02:38.739
After the atoll.

1108
02:02:39.779 --> 02:02:41.937
when I offered myself to you.

1109
02:02:45.253 --> 02:02:47.071
why didn't you take me?

1110
02:02:49.660 --> 02:02:51.748
'Cause you didn't
really want me.

1111
02:02:54.000 --> 02:02:55.353
Not really.

1112
02:04:01.049 --> 02:04:02.730
Have I been
asleep long?

1113
02:04:09.000 --> 02:04:10.466
I was dreaming.

1114
02:04:13.642 --> 02:04:14.939
It's funny.

1115
02:04:16.614 --> 02:04:18.708
I always thought
Dryland floated.

1116
02:04:19.387 --> 02:04:23.257
That it drifted with the wind.
That's why it was so hard to find.

1117
02:04:23.461 --> 02:04:25.726
Why did you believe
in it so much?

1118
02:04:27.035 --> 02:04:29.368
Because we weren't
made for the sea.

1119
02:04:30.909 --> 02:04:34.176
Got hands and feet.

1120
02:04:34.249 --> 02:04:35.979
We're supposed to walk.

1121
02:04:39.927 --> 02:04:41.519
I miss her sound.

1122
02:04:44.202 --> 02:04:45.395
Don't you?

1123
02:04:46.339 --> 02:04:49.309
Might be able to get
some hydro out of this.

1124
02:04:49.480 --> 02:04:51.004
I can't go on.

1125
02:04:52.920 --> 02:04:55.481
Not without her.
or Dryland.

1126
02:04:56.727 --> 02:04:59.755
I don't want to live
if there's nothing left.

1127
02:05:00.602 --> 02:05:02.229
There's no hope.

1128
02:05:03.105 --> 02:05:04.800
You're still here.

1129
02:05:12.157 --> 02:05:14.091
Thank you for saving me.

1130
02:05:14.162 --> 02:05:16.290
You can thank the ancients.

1131
02:05:17.936 --> 02:05:19.837
This is what they had.

1132
02:05:20.775 --> 02:05:23.005
This is what
they made of it.

1133
02:05:23.647 --> 02:05:25.707
That's why
I am what I am.

1134
02:05:26.051 --> 02:05:28.680
I may not be human.
but I don't quit.

1135
02:05:29.258 --> 02:05:30.657
Never have.

1136
02:05:31.596 --> 02:05:33.622
No matter what
they throw at me. I...

1137
02:06:05.563 --> 02:06:06.756
Helen!

1138
02:06:07.567 --> 02:06:08.931
Helen!

1139
02:06:09.571 --> 02:06:12.838
No. no. no. Helen. up here. Above you!

1140
02:06:14.013 --> 02:06:15.206
Gregor!

1141
02:06:20.025 --> 02:06:22.426
Smart thinking.
to burn your boat.

1142
02:06:22.496 --> 02:06:26.264
Without the smoke. I
never would have found you.

1143
02:06:26.337 --> 02:06:28.465
Who's that with you?

1144
02:06:28.542 --> 02:06:31.809
Ichthyus sapien.
is that really you?

1145
02:06:32.684 --> 02:06:36.520
I'll throw the rope down. You
catch it. I'll help you climb up.

1146
02:06:38.294 --> 02:06:42.426
Helen. Where's Enola?

1147
02:06:42.502 --> 02:06:47.466
Smokers took her. They'd have
me. too. if it weren't for him.

1148
02:06:47.546 --> 02:06:51.508
My friend. thank you.
Very human of you.

1149
02:06:53.257 --> 02:06:55.749
Well. grab your things
quickly. Quickly. Come.

1150
02:07:04.178 --> 02:07:06.272
You see?
Right down there.

1151
02:07:06.350 --> 02:07:09.720
There's several of us survivors.
We'll just start over again.

1152
02:07:12.862 --> 02:07:16.459
Don't worry. they'll welcome
you. just like Gregor did.

1153
02:07:33.905 --> 02:07:35.566
You can't ask us
to go get her!

1154
02:07:35.641 --> 02:07:37.268
Enola's the reason
we're in all this trouble.

1155
02:07:37.344 --> 02:07:38.674
Forget it!
We're not going.

1156
02:07:38.747 --> 02:07:40.374
They don't have
any reason to kill her.

1157
02:07:40.450 --> 02:07:42.851
They need to find
Dryland just like we do.

1158
02:07:42.922 --> 02:07:44.321
Of course.

1159
02:07:44.392 --> 02:07:47.055
If the Mariner's
willing to go. why not us?

1160
02:07:47.130 --> 02:07:48.825
If he wants
to go. then let him!

1161
02:07:48.900 --> 02:07:51.426
We don't want
you here! You or the girl!

1162
02:07:52.474 --> 02:07:56.971
Helen. The papers the
Mariner brought you...

1163
02:07:57.050 --> 02:08:00.647
It's the same language
the tattoo is written in.

1164
02:08:01.392 --> 02:08:06.629
Eighty-six. 56. 27. 59...

1165
02:08:07.069 --> 02:08:09.231
If I can figure out what
these numbers refer to...

1166
02:08:09.307 --> 02:08:10.865
They refer to nothing.

1167
02:08:10.944 --> 02:08:12.069
What?

1168
02:08:12.145 --> 02:08:13.737
Dryland doesn't exist.

1169
02:08:13.816 --> 02:08:15.613
Gregor. you're as crazy as she is!

1170
02:08:15.685 --> 02:08:16.878
We can't stay here!

1171
02:08:16.956 --> 02:08:20.553
We're wasting valuable time. More Smokers
will come. We need to be moving now!

1172
02:08:20.630 --> 02:08:24.865
My friends. don't you see we need
this child if we want to find Dryland?

1173
02:08:24.938 --> 02:08:27.237
I'm not going.
I say let them go.

1174
02:08:27.309 --> 02:08:29.972
We're better off
without them. anyway!

1175
02:08:39.000 --> 02:08:41.325
You won't go
after her. either?

1176
02:08:44.658 --> 02:08:47.482
I thought you were
different. I am different.

1177
02:08:50.382 --> 02:08:52.707
Hey.
Hey! That's my sail!

1178
02:08:53.310 --> 02:08:55.362
What's he doing?
Leaving.

1179
02:08:56.106 --> 02:08:58.090
Not on one of our boats...

1180
02:08:59.134 --> 02:09:01.958
You can give it to him.
or he'll take it.

1181
02:09:15.306 --> 02:09:17.529
Enola said
you were her friend.

1182
02:09:18.369 --> 02:09:21.124
What do I tell her
when I see her again?

1183
02:09:22.563 --> 02:09:23.650
Lies.

1184
02:09:25.989 --> 02:09:28.143
If it makes you feel better.

1185
02:09:41.365 --> 02:09:42.986
Don't blame him.

1186
02:09:43.362 --> 02:09:45.380
Survival is all he knows.

1187
02:09:46.224 --> 02:09:49.445
That's why someday there
will be so many like him.

1188
02:09:49.785 --> 02:09:51.679
and probably
so few of us.

1189
02:11:45.000 --> 02:11:46.535
What do you want?

1190
02:11:47.555 --> 02:11:49.365
All kinds of things.

1191
02:11:50.145 --> 02:11:52.219
But right now.

1192
02:11:53.609 --> 02:11:56.188
we'll settle for
everything you've got.

1193
02:11:56.266 --> 02:11:58.214
Ain't that right. Bone?

1194
02:11:58.318 --> 02:12:01.608
You've already destroyed our homes.
Why can't you just leave us alone?

1195
02:12:01.680 --> 02:12:04.637
I don't know.
Character thing. I guess.

1196
02:12:05.684 --> 02:12:07.632
Ain't that right. Bone?

1197
02:12:09.047 --> 02:12:11.327
Bone? Bone?

1198
02:12:29.733 --> 02:12:31.647
I'm going after Enola.

1199
02:12:41.000 --> 02:12:44.585
You know. for a hideous
freak. you're okay.

1200
02:12:45.760 --> 02:12:47.585
It was a joke!

1201
02:12:49.488 --> 02:12:50.882
Know what that is yet?

1202
02:12:50.951 --> 02:12:52.742
What. the numbers?
Yes. I think I do.

1203
02:12:52.816 --> 02:12:56.401
It seems to be some ancient
form of geographic location.

1204
02:12:56.478 --> 02:12:57.997
latitude. longitude.

1205
02:12:58.075 --> 02:12:59.628
It doesn't make
sense. though.

1206
02:12:59.705 --> 02:13:02.926
The numbers. they seem to
be backwards or something.

1207
02:13:03.000 --> 02:13:05.314
It's upside down.
The world?

1208
02:13:05.389 --> 02:13:08.041
The poles have
reversed themselves?

1209
02:13:08.120 --> 02:13:10.329
I've been mapping
the cities below.

1210
02:13:13.000 --> 02:13:16.725
The world wasn't created in a
deluge. It was covered by it.

1211
02:13:16.803 --> 02:13:20.013
That's blasphemy!
No. it's true.

1212
02:13:20.092 --> 02:13:25.020
I've seen it with my own eyes. There
is land. It's right under our keel.

1213
02:13:25.093 --> 02:13:27.310
None of it's dry anymore.
Some is.

1214
02:13:29.000 --> 02:13:38.317
Enola's been there. I know
that now. I saw what she drew.

1215
02:13:39.000 --> 02:13:41.964
This is ridiculous.
Going after the Smokers?

1216
02:13:42.039 --> 02:13:44.645
He doesn't even know which
direction they came from.

1217
02:14:06.000 --> 02:14:08.530
If she's alive.
I'll bring her back to you.

1218
02:14:16.290 --> 02:14:20.451
Forget the mute-o. Helen. If
he brings her back. they'll kill us all!

1219
02:14:20.522 --> 02:14:24.417
I can't stand it. We gotta go help
him. I can't ask him to do this alone.

1220
02:14:24.494 --> 02:14:28.267
Oh. don't worry. my dear.
You're not going to have to.

1221
02:14:44.000 --> 02:14:45.636
Hey. Doc. what's this here? Where?

1222
02:14:45.712 --> 02:14:47.519
Right there. above the
squiggle. What. there?

1223
02:14:47.594 --> 02:14:49.573
Looks like a star.
Or a meteor.

1224
02:14:49.642 --> 02:14:51.083
It's a mole.

1225
02:14:51.389 --> 02:14:53.872
You got that tattoo
figured out yet?

1226
02:14:53.940 --> 02:14:56.985
It would be easier if it
was flat. big and flat.

1227
02:14:57.065 --> 02:14:59.915
It needs to be flat.
What you got in mind?

1228
02:14:59.986 --> 02:15:06.054
Well. you cut it off her back. You stretch
it. mount it. Give us a proper look.

1229
02:15:06.133 --> 02:15:08.376
Take her down
below until I holler.

1230
02:15:09.827 --> 02:15:11.738
Saint Joe. we're close.

1231
02:15:13.388 --> 02:15:15.527
After centuries of shame.

1232
02:16:53.003 --> 02:16:54.707
They're getting ugly.

1233
02:16:54.784 --> 02:16:55.984
Don't I know it.

1234
02:16:57.000 --> 02:16:59.130
Announce me. cousin.

1235
02:17:03.487 --> 02:17:05.184
Hey. Here he is.

1236
02:17:05.260 --> 02:17:07.059
Deacon!

1237
02:17:07.132 --> 02:17:09.866
Rise up.
brothers and sisters.

1238
02:17:11.446 --> 02:17:14.820
Turn your eyes
and open your hearts

1239
02:17:14.890 --> 02:17:17.293
to your humble benefactor.

1240
02:17:17.365 --> 02:17:21.103
your spiritual shepherd
and dictator for life.

1241
02:17:21.177 --> 02:17:23.911
the Deacon of the 'Deez.

1242
02:17:55.588 --> 02:17:57.148
Deacon!

1243
02:18:17.390 --> 02:18:21.265
Children. Children
of the provider.

1244
02:18:22.841 --> 02:18:26.841
Citizens of the good ship.
Please. now. hear me speak.

1245
02:18:30.935 --> 02:18:32.301
I've had a vision.

1246
02:18:32.372 --> 02:18:33.966
Yeah. we're tired
of your visions!

1247
02:18:34.044 --> 02:18:35.947
What about the land
you promised us?

1248
02:18:36.019 --> 02:18:39.084
Yeah!
Yeah!

1249
02:18:39.161 --> 02:18:41.725
Oh. ye of little faith.

1250
02:18:42.104 --> 02:18:44.074
I've had a vision so great

1251
02:18:44.144 --> 02:18:47.551
that as it came to me.
I wept.

1252
02:18:47.622 --> 02:18:49.958
And in this splenditudinous
figment of wonder...

1253
02:18:50.029 --> 02:18:51.292
Is that Bone's ride?

1254
02:18:51.367 --> 02:18:53.931
Is that blood on the seat?... I saw.

1255
02:18:54.009 --> 02:18:57.747
And you know what
it is that I saw.

1256
02:18:57.821 --> 02:19:02.061
I saw the land.

1257
02:19:03.506 --> 02:19:04.872
Dryland! Dryland!
Dryland! Dryland!

1258
02:19:29.322 --> 02:19:31.521
Dryland! Dryland!
Dryland! Dryland!

1259
02:19:31.595 --> 02:19:33.794
Dryland! Dryland!
Dryland! Dryland!

1260
02:19:42.599 --> 02:19:43.965
Horse. that you?

1261
02:19:49.386 --> 02:19:52.885
Look. just bring it in slow.
okay? I don't have all day.

1262
02:19:55.138 --> 02:19:56.333
Horse!

1263
02:19:56.410 --> 02:19:58.004
Just bring it up slow.

1264
02:19:59.887 --> 02:20:01.619
I said slow! No!

1265
02:20:20.454 --> 02:20:22.253
You killed Smitty. cousin.

1266
02:20:26.071 --> 02:20:27.563
Nice landing.

1267
02:20:28.712 --> 02:20:31.048
Smitty. man!
Always in the way!

1268
02:20:35.034 --> 02:20:37.130
Smitty? I quit!

1269
02:20:39.247 --> 02:20:41.742
I'm in charge now. baby!

1270
02:20:41.822 --> 02:20:44.123
Come on. move!
Move! I'm in charge!

1271
02:20:44.197 --> 02:20:46.430
I'm in charge!
No way!

1272
02:20:52.992 --> 02:20:56.366
And he said
this to me personally.

1273
02:20:58.508 --> 02:21:02.543
We are to go there.
and we are to settle it.

1274
02:21:03.057 --> 02:21:05.051
And we are to build a...

1275
02:21:06.367 --> 02:21:09.706
Shouldn't be doing that.
You're gonna get in trouble.

1276
02:21:10.949 --> 02:21:12.475
That's right.

1277
02:21:12.554 --> 02:21:13.886
You're not afraid.

1278
02:21:13.958 --> 02:21:16.727
You've got your pet freak
coming to rescue you.

1279
02:21:16.802 --> 02:21:19.001
He's not a freak. and
he can take you anytime.

1280
02:21:21.282 --> 02:21:25.488
He's killed dozens of people. and he
doesn't have any mercy or anything.

1281
02:21:25.963 --> 02:21:28.059
He even kills little girls.

1282
02:21:29.843 --> 02:21:31.005
Haven't we all?

1283
02:21:32.987 --> 02:21:34.114
Dang.

1284
02:21:35.393 --> 02:21:36.520
It's Horse.

1285
02:21:37.601 --> 02:21:38.627
Horse?

1286
02:21:38.705 --> 02:21:41.108
Find him. Find him!
Come on!

1287
02:21:43.253 --> 02:21:45.554
Yes! Yes! Yes!

1288
02:21:45.995 --> 02:21:47.727
Come on.

1289
02:21:47.800 --> 02:21:49.770
Getting nervous.
aren't you?

1290
02:21:53.618 --> 02:21:55.086
I don't get nervous.

1291
02:21:56.930 --> 02:21:59.596
And if there's
a river. we'll dam it.

1292
02:21:59.672 --> 02:22:03.547
And if there's a tree.
we'll ram it.

1293
02:22:04.386 --> 02:22:07.120
'Cause I'm talking
progress here.

1294
02:22:07.196 --> 02:22:10.433
Yes. sir.
I'm talking development.

1295
02:22:10.506 --> 02:22:11.532
Yeah!

1296
02:22:11.610 --> 02:22:16.420
For we shall suck
and savor the sweet flavor

1297
02:22:16.493 --> 02:22:18.726
of Dryland.

1298
02:22:19.435 --> 02:22:21.167
Your face is all red.

1299
02:22:22.812 --> 02:22:25.981
Helen said with anybody
that has a face that red.

1300
02:22:26.057 --> 02:22:28.460
he's either had too much
sun or too much to drink.

1301
02:22:28.531 --> 02:22:31.129
All right. that's it.
I'm gonna burn your face.

1302
02:22:31.206 --> 02:22:32.505
Almost time.

1303
02:22:34.049 --> 02:22:35.517
What's up?

1304
02:22:35.587 --> 02:22:37.352
We're just talking
about her friend.

1305
02:22:39.065 --> 02:22:42.370
What's his name?
He doesn't have a name.

1306
02:22:42.442 --> 02:22:44.504
So death can't find him.

1307
02:22:50.000 --> 02:22:52.954
Doesn't have a home
or people to care for.

1308
02:22:54.374 --> 02:22:58.540
He's not afraid of anything.
men least of all.

1309
02:22:58.630 --> 02:23:02.449
He's fast and strong
like a big wind.

1310
02:23:02.535 --> 02:23:06.514
He can hear 100 miles
and see 100 miles underwater.

1311
02:23:06.637 --> 02:23:11.308
He could be right behind you. and you
won't even know it till you're dead!

1312
02:23:14.056 --> 02:23:15.531
Give it a rest.

1313
02:23:18.000 --> 02:23:20.022
He'll come for me.
He will.

1314
02:23:20.099 --> 02:23:22.757
We are the reason.
Yeah?

1315
02:23:22.834 --> 02:23:24.458
Well. I hope he does.

1316
02:23:24.533 --> 02:23:25.997
The Lord's creation.

1317
02:23:28.000 --> 02:23:29.701
Remember you said that.

1318
02:23:30.582 --> 02:23:32.283
Look at us.

1319
02:23:33.230 --> 02:23:35.708
Look at us here today.
Yeah!

1320
02:23:35.777 --> 02:23:39.490
Dryland is not just
our destination.

1321
02:23:40.134 --> 02:23:42.669
but it is our destiny!

1322
02:23:51.330 --> 02:23:53.865
Find him. Find him!

1323
02:23:53.944 --> 02:23:58.262
"How can I find
this glorious place?"

1324
02:23:59.441 --> 02:24:01.244
And he said to me.

1325
02:24:02.391 --> 02:24:06.607
"A child shall lead you."

1326
02:24:07.788 --> 02:24:10.095
A child.

1327
02:24:10.168 --> 02:24:11.503
And behold!

1328
02:24:11.576 --> 02:24:12.842
It's time.

1329
02:24:12.916 --> 02:24:15.760
The instrument
of our salvation!

1330
02:24:22.905 --> 02:24:25.509
Our guide in the wild.

1331
02:24:25.585 --> 02:24:27.927
Our beacon in the darkness.

1332
02:24:28.000 --> 02:24:30.016
Turn her around. Nord.

1333
02:24:30.089 --> 02:24:33.007
She has shown me the path!

1334
02:24:37.469 --> 02:24:41.290
And before the holy-most
moment is upon us.

1335
02:24:41.787 --> 02:24:45.679
let's sacrifice
one to old Saint Joe.

1336
02:24:48.819 --> 02:24:51.701
And let's get this tub
of junk up to speed.

1337
02:24:58.741 --> 02:24:59.879
Yeah.

1338
02:25:40.031 --> 02:25:41.762
Pull!

1339
02:25:41.843 --> 02:25:45.105
Pull!
Pull!

1340
02:25:45.186 --> 02:25:47.439
Pull.
Pull!

1341
02:26:02.628 --> 02:26:04.181
So which way we rowing?

1342
02:26:04.264 --> 02:26:06.067
I don't have a damn clue.

1343
02:26:06.143 --> 02:26:07.946
Don't worry.

1344
02:26:08.023 --> 02:26:11.357
They'll row for a month before
they figure out I'm faking it.

1345
02:26:11.436 --> 02:26:14.354
But why?

1346
02:26:14.431 --> 02:26:16.020
Oh. you want details.

1347
02:26:16.102 --> 02:26:19.923
Well. I'm not telling these savages
that we haven't solved the map yet.

1348
02:26:20.000 --> 02:26:21.390
I promised them results.

1349
02:26:21.460 --> 02:26:24.876
and I'll get them if I gotta
cut them out of her back.

1350
02:26:27.535 --> 02:26:30.045
Who is that?
Who is that?

1351
02:26:31.617 --> 02:26:34.071
Maybe one of
the spare rowers?

1352
02:26:41.871 --> 02:26:43.793
Why aren't you rowing?

1353
02:26:53.156 --> 02:26:55.045
It's him.
It is him.

1354
02:26:56.342 --> 02:26:58.490
You guys
are in so much trouble.

1355
02:27:01.850 --> 02:27:05.028
Well. I'll be damned.
It's the gentleman guppy.

1356
02:27:06.231 --> 02:27:08.776
You know. he's like
a toilet that won't flush.

1357
02:27:09.948 --> 02:27:11.338
I want the girl.

1358
02:27:15.258 --> 02:27:19.896
You know. I thought
you were stupid. friend.

1359
02:27:21.000 --> 02:27:23.425
But I underestimated you.

1360
02:27:23.733 --> 02:27:26.020
You're a total slime-o.

1361
02:27:29.806 --> 02:27:33.543
I want the girl.
That's all.

1362
02:27:33.618 --> 02:27:37.689
Well. what on this screwed-up earth
makes you think you're gonna get her?

1363
02:27:46.236 --> 02:27:48.017
You know what this is?

1364
02:27:52.544 --> 02:27:55.131
I drop it. you burn.

1365
02:27:55.615 --> 02:27:57.396
We all burn.

1366
02:27:57.470 --> 02:27:59.078
Now. wait.
wait. wait. wait.

1367
02:28:00.507 --> 02:28:03.163
Let's not do
anything rash here.

1368
02:28:03.239 --> 02:28:05.791
I mean. are you sure
she's worth all this?

1369
02:28:05.872 --> 02:28:09.069
She never does stop talking.
She never shuts up.

1370
02:28:09.818 --> 02:28:10.920
I noticed.

1371
02:28:11.000 --> 02:28:12.929
What is it. then?

1372
02:28:13.499 --> 02:28:14.962
It's the map.

1373
02:28:15.864 --> 02:28:17.191
She's my friend.

1374
02:28:18.631 --> 02:28:21.652
Golly gee. A single tear
rolls down my cheek.

1375
02:28:21.729 --> 02:28:24.193
I mean. you're gonna die
for your friend?

1376
02:28:26.060 --> 02:28:27.490
If it comes to that.

1377
02:28:29.858 --> 02:28:31.720
He's bluffing.
I'll kill him.

1378
02:28:31.791 --> 02:28:33.948
He's not bluffing.
He never bluffs.

1379
02:28:34.024 --> 02:28:35.318
Shut up!

1380
02:28:37.689 --> 02:28:41.482
I don't think you're gonna
drop that torch. my friend.

1381
02:28:42.355 --> 02:28:43.785
Why not?

1382
02:28:43.854 --> 02:28:45.545
Because you're not crazy.

1383
02:28:49.219 --> 02:28:50.274
No!

1384
02:28:59.515 --> 02:29:00.537
Oh. thank God.

1385
02:29:19.641 --> 02:29:21.570
Look out!
Look out!

1386
02:29:21.641 --> 02:29:23.071
That's him!

1387
02:29:24.173 --> 02:29:25.431
Let's go!

1388
02:29:29.470 --> 02:29:32.297
Don't just stand there!
Kill something!

1389
02:29:35.369 --> 02:29:37.095
Was this your big vision?

1390
02:29:47.198 --> 02:29:49.628
I've always wanted
to drive this monster.

1391
02:29:52.963 --> 02:29:55.324
There he is!
There he is!

1392
02:29:59.459 --> 02:30:01.218
That's him! There!

1393
02:30:22.052 --> 02:30:24.913
Let go! Let go!

1394
02:30:35.081 --> 02:30:36.306
I said. let go!

1395
02:30:40.912 --> 02:30:43.773
Let me go! Let go!

1396
02:30:43.877 --> 02:30:46.636
Let me go! Let go!
Pilot!

1397
02:30:46.710 --> 02:30:48.833
Pilot!
Let me go!

1398
02:30:51.675 --> 02:30:53.332
Pilot!
Let me go!

1399
02:30:53.408 --> 02:30:54.531
Let go!

1400
02:30:58.906 --> 02:31:01.165
You should've
stayed underwater.

1401
02:31:11.502 --> 02:31:14.659
Now. you know how to fly an
airplane? Lucky I do. huh?

1402
02:31:16.000 --> 02:31:18.493
Now. you stop it!
You behave yourself. now!

1403
02:32:53.937 --> 02:32:55.599
It's going down.

1404
02:32:55.674 --> 02:32:57.005
You can
see it sinking.

1405
02:32:57.079 --> 02:33:00.210
Gregor. bring us
right down on top of it.

1406
02:33:00.720 --> 02:33:02.814
Hurry. Gregor!
Don't worry.

1407
02:33:02.892 --> 02:33:03.917
Hurry.

1408
02:33:18.062 --> 02:33:20.328
Enola! Up here!

1409
02:33:20.401 --> 02:33:21.699
Grab on!

1410
02:33:27.185 --> 02:33:28.916
Are they on yet?

1411
02:33:32.564 --> 02:33:34.761
What is it?
I don't know!

1412
02:33:46.899 --> 02:33:51.136
Got you! I'm gonna rip
your cute little lungs out.

1413
02:34:06.280 --> 02:34:08.306
Pull! Almost.

1414
02:34:48.314 --> 02:34:51.080
No! Enola!
No!

1415
02:34:53.326 --> 02:34:55.922
Saint Joe. Hole in one.

1416
02:34:56.000 --> 02:34:58.592
Helen!
No! Enola!

1417
02:34:58.670 --> 02:34:59.966
Helen!

1418
02:35:00.404 --> 02:35:02.394
Hey! Hey!

1419
02:35:06.443 --> 02:35:10.173
If I can't have Dryland.
no one will!

1420
02:35:15.018 --> 02:35:17.814
Oh. no! Quick!
What are we gonna do?

1421
02:35:21.225 --> 02:35:22.315
Tie this off.

1422
02:35:27.331 --> 02:35:29.263
Hurry!
Tie it!

1423
02:35:35.172 --> 02:35:36.331
Got it!

1424
02:35:50.119 --> 02:35:51.482
Get them up now.

1425
02:36:09.871 --> 02:36:11.234
Of course.

1426
02:36:13.342 --> 02:36:15.274
Of course. The numbers.

1427
02:36:15.644 --> 02:36:19.943
The numbers!
They must be it!

1428
02:36:21.216 --> 02:36:22.203
What?

1429
02:36:22.284 --> 02:36:23.580
I was swimming.

1430
02:36:24.520 --> 02:36:26.748
I saw.
My friends.

1431
02:36:26.822 --> 02:36:28.788
My friends. look.

1432
02:36:30.392 --> 02:36:33.154
This map... This map.

1433
02:36:33.228 --> 02:36:36.093
it bears a grid system with
numbers the ancients used

1434
02:36:36.164 --> 02:36:39.097
to determine geographic
location on the world.

1435
02:36:39.468 --> 02:36:43.062
Just like the numbers and
the symbols on Enola's back.

1436
02:36:44.673 --> 02:36:49.267
First they would determine the
angle of the sun using this.

1437
02:36:49.344 --> 02:36:51.572
and that would tell them where
they were located on the grid

1438
02:36:51.646 --> 02:36:54.170
and which direction
they had to go.

1439
02:36:56.817 --> 02:36:58.646
If I take a bearing
from the sun

1440
02:36:58.719 --> 02:37:01.584
and reverse the coordinates
on Enola's back.

1441
02:37:03.858 --> 02:37:05.949
then Dryland is that way!

1442
02:39:10.248 --> 02:39:11.577
It's fresh!

1443
02:39:11.649 --> 02:39:14.309
All of this!
It's fresh!

1444
02:39:30.167 --> 02:39:32.133
I found something!

1445
02:40:31.393 --> 02:40:33.791
Maybe we should put
them under the dirt.

1446
02:40:34.897 --> 02:40:36.625
I think
it was their way.

1447
02:40:39.034 --> 02:40:41.365
They must have
known they were dying.

1448
02:41:12.000 --> 02:41:13.296
I'm home.

1449
02:41:24.713 --> 02:41:27.305
Where's the Mariner?
He was outside.

1450
02:41:32.320 --> 02:41:34.787
Wait. Wait!
I want to show you this.

1451
02:42:53.265 --> 02:42:55.959
First time in your life
you got nothing to say?

1452
02:43:10.349 --> 02:43:12.042
Enola. I have to go now.

1453
02:43:13.219 --> 02:43:14.947
But you came back
for me.

1454
02:43:17.056 --> 02:43:18.352
I like you.

1455
02:43:23.995 --> 02:43:25.585
Why are you leaving?

1456
02:43:29.101 --> 02:43:31.295
I don't belong here.
I belong out there.

1457
02:43:31.369 --> 02:43:32.925
You belong here.

1458
02:43:35.708 --> 02:43:38.334
It's too strange here.
It doesn't move right.

1459
02:43:39.109 --> 02:43:42.009
Helen said that
it's only landsickness.

1460
02:43:42.881 --> 02:43:45.746
We're all feeling it.
It'll go away soon.

1461
02:43:46.584 --> 02:43:48.140
It's more than that.

1462
02:44:36.333 --> 02:44:38.390
Well. goodbye.
my friend.

1463
02:44:40.770 --> 02:44:43.430
Oh. I have
something for you.

1464
02:44:44.741 --> 02:44:46.104
It's dirt.

1465
02:44:47.777 --> 02:44:50.141
Don't trade it
all in one place.

1466
02:44:52.081 --> 02:44:53.273
Or do!

1467
02:44:53.382 --> 02:44:56.349
It'll give you reason
to come back for more!

1468
02:45:00.222 --> 02:45:02.154
It's all I got.
Drifter.

1469
02:45:03.059 --> 02:45:04.581
It's enough.

1470
02:45:13.736 --> 02:45:16.931
Is it that easy for you
to just drift away?

1471
02:45:17.006 --> 02:45:18.938
Never said it was easy.

1472
02:45:21.143 --> 02:45:22.904
I don't understand.

1473
02:45:28.850 --> 02:45:30.645
I don't understand.

1474
02:45:32.154 --> 02:45:33.483
I mean. you brought us here.

1475
02:45:33.555 --> 02:45:36.181
You belong here as much
as anyone. maybe more.

1476
02:45:42.564 --> 02:45:44.723
What do you think
you're going to find?

1477
02:45:44.799 --> 02:45:47.163
What are you looking for
out there?

1478
02:45:47.434 --> 02:45:51.028
Gregor once said there might
be others like me somewhere.

1479
02:45:52.941 --> 02:45:54.497
I have to know.

1480
02:45:57.278 --> 02:46:01.110
Helen. if I find any
others out there like you.

1481
02:46:03.785 --> 02:46:06.149
I'll tell them
about this place.

1482
02:46:06.454 --> 02:46:10.014
and how one woman with hope
and courage found it.

1483
02:46:50.631 --> 02:46:52.655
I have something for you.

1484
02:46:54.101 --> 02:46:56.329
something you'll need
on your journey.

1485
02:46:56.402 --> 02:46:58.664
I don't have much
to barter with.

1486
02:46:58.738 --> 02:47:00.863
It's no trade.
It's a gift.

1487
02:47:02.175 --> 02:47:03.765
No such thing in Waterworld.

1488
02:47:03.843 --> 02:47:06.276
Well. then let this
be the first.

1489
02:47:07.814 --> 02:47:09.246
It's a name.

1490
02:47:10.349 --> 02:47:14.512
It's from an old story about a
great warrior returning from battle.

1491
02:47:14.986 --> 02:47:18.078
He just set sail. and
the water god cursed him.

1492
02:47:18.624 --> 02:47:20.886
and for the next 10 years.
he drifted on the seas.

1493
02:47:20.960 --> 02:47:24.291
The warrior drifted on the seas.
unable to find his way home.

1494
02:47:24.363 --> 02:47:27.125
until finally the gods
took pity on him.

1495
02:47:28.167 --> 02:47:32.694
and they called up a warm wind
that blew him home to his family.

1496
02:47:34.340 --> 02:47:36.568
and he never
left them again.

1497
02:47:39.578 --> 02:47:41.407
His name was Ulysses.

1498
02:47:45.083 --> 02:47:46.708
It's a good name.

1499
02:47:47.305 --> 02:48:47.341
